{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FtKbrVYAmiAGSqE3Rh57Sb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# HYPOTHESIS: Multi-Objective Constrained CMA-ES with ITL Penalty\n     2→\n     3→**Round:** 4\n     4→**Idea:** 1 — Constrained CMA-ES\n     5→**Date:** 2026-03-02\n     6→**Status:** Pending\n     7→\n     8→## Context and Prior Findings\n     9→\n    10→Round 3's CMA-ES (Idea 3 H1) achieved 15.1% mean E2E with 4/10 experiments below 10% — the best E2E result in the research program. However, it sacrificed ITL accuracy: 87.4% mean ITL (was 9.5% in the trace replay baseline). The root cause is the unconstrained single-objective formulation — CMA-ES inflated `output_token_processing_time_us` to implausible values (e.g., 7B: 0 → 1,899μs) as a proxy for missing simulation dynamics.\n    11→\n    12→This idea adds three modifications to the R3 CMA-ES approach:\n    13→1. **ITL penalty term** in the objective function\n    14→2. **Parameter bounds** constraining physically implausible values\n    15→3. **Integrated TTFT corrections** (from R3 H3) applied during optimization rather than post-hoc\n    16→\n    17→### Related Work\n    18→\n    19→- Deb et al., 2002 — NSGA-II for multi-objective evolutionary optimization\n    20→- Igel et al., 2007 — MO-CMA-ES for multi-objective optimization with CMA-ES\n    21→- R3 Idea 3 — unconstrained CMA-ES achieving 15.1% E2E / 87.4% ITL\n    22→\n    23→## Sub-Hypotheses\n    24→\n    25→### H1: Constrained CMA-ES with ITL Penalty → Joint E2E + ITL\n    26→\n    27→**Claim:** A penalty-augmented CMA-ES objective (`objective = 0.5*e2e + 0.5*itl + penalty`) with constrained parameter bounds achieves **mean E2E < 15% AND mean ITL < 25%** simultaneously across 10 experiments.\n    28→\n    29→**Refutation criteria:** Mean E2E > 18% (worse than R3 by >3pp) OR mean ITL > 30%.\n    30→\n    31→**Method:**\n    32→1. Start from R3's optimized artifacts as initial CMA-ES population\n    33→2. Add parameter bounds: `output_token_processing_time_us ∈ [0, 500]`, `scheduling_processing_time_us ∈ [0, 2000]`, `step_overhead_us ∈ [model_baseline × 0.8, model_baseline × 3.0]`\n    34→3. Dual-metric objective: `f(x) = 0.5 * mean_e2e_error + 0.5 * mean_itl_error + 10.0 * max(0, mean_itl_error - 0.20)`\n    35→4. Apply TTFT additive corrections (per-model, from R3 H3) inside the objective evaluation loop\n    36→5. Run per-model optimization with CMA-ES (σ₀ = 0.1, ~100 evaluations per model)\n    37→6. Run with three α values (0.7, 0.5, 0.3 on the E2E weight) to explore the Pareto frontier\n    38→\n    39→**Data split:** No training/test split for CMA-ES — it optimizes against BLIS E2E on all 10 experiments simultaneously. Generalization tested via LOMO/LOWO.\n    40→\n    41→### H2: Pareto Sweep Identifies Knee Point\n    42→\n    43→**Claim:** Running CMA-ES with different E2E/ITL weight ratios produces a Pareto frontier where at least one configuration achieves **E2E < 12% AND ITL < 20%** — a result that R3's single-objective could not achieve.\n    44→\n    45→**Refutation criteria:** No Pareto point achieves both E2E < 15% and ITL < 25%.\n    46→\n    47→**Method:**\n    48→1. Run H1 with α ∈ {0.7, 0.5, 0.3} (weighting E2E vs ITL)\n    49→2. Collect per-experiment E2E and ITL errors for each α\n    50→3. Plot Pareto frontier: E2E vs ITL\n    51→4. Select knee point (closest to the origin) as the recommended configuration\n    52→\n    53→### H3: LOMO Generalization (Cross-Model Artifact Transfer)\n    54→\n    55→**Claim:** Constrained CMA-ES artifacts transfer across models with **mean best-donor E2E < 20%** (vs R3's 14.8% with unconstrained CMA-ES). Constraining the parameter space should maintain cross-model transferability while improving ITL.\n    56→\n    57→**Refutation criteria:** Mean best-donor E2E > 30% (2× worse than R3 LOMO).\n    58→\n    59→**Method:**\n    60→1. For each model group, apply the CMA-ES-optimized artifacts from other models\n    61→2. Evaluate BLIS E2E and ITL per experiment\n    62→3. Build cross-model transfer matrix (same as R3 H5)\n    63→4. Use `hypotheses/h-stepml/shared/splits.py:leave_one_model_out()` for data splitting\n    64→\n    65→### H4: LOWO Generalization (Cross-Workload Stability)\n    66→\n    67→**Claim:** Constrained CMA-ES artifacts show per-model workload variance **≤ 20pp** (range across workloads) for dense models, with **mean E2E within 2× of aggregate** for all 10 experiments.\n    68→\n    69→**Refutation criteria:** More than 2/10 experiments exceed 2× aggregate E2E error.\n    70→\n    71→**Method:**\n    72→1. Evaluate per-experiment E2E/ITL from H1's best configuration\n    73→2. Group by model, compute per-workload breakdown\n    74→3. Measure range (max-min) per model\n    75→4. Use `hypotheses/h-stepml/shared/splits.py:leave_one_workload_out()` for data splitting\n    76→\n    77→## Execution Plan\n    78→\n    79→1. H1 first — constrained CMA-ES per model with dual objective\n    80→2. H2 — Pareto sweep (runs H1 with different α values)\n    81→3. H3 — LOMO using H1's best artifacts\n    82→4. H4 — LOWO from H1's results\n    83→\n    84→## Short-Circuit Criteria\n    85→\n    86→If H1 produces mean E2E > 25% (significantly worse than R3's 15.1%), the constrained approach is harming more than helping — abort remaining hypotheses and document root cause.\n    87→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017vgie1jSaXiJSc9cebn2B7","session_id":"6c146fd0-2769-4d18-b481-0819d4602c26","uuid":"39d50281-8853-41cb-aac2-083483b6e0bb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017DDLKhGBihqPjtNSMfmKks","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# FINDINGS SUMMARY: Idea 3 — End-to-End Calibration via Direct E2E Objective\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-02-27\n     4→**Status:** Partially successful — CMA-ES achieves 15.1% mean E2E with 4/10 < 10%; specific models (codellama-34b, llama-2-70b) reach production quality\n     5→\n     6→## 1. Idea Recap\n     7→\n     8→This idea jointly calibrates all LatencyModel coefficients by directly minimizing BLIS E2E mean error using CMA-ES (Covariance Matrix Adaptation Evolution Strategy), bypassing per-component accuracy. The approach treats BLIS as a black-box function mapping artifact parameters → E2E error and optimizes per-model coefficient vectors (~16-23 parameters) against trace-replay experiments.\n     9→\n    10→**Starting point:** Round 2's best regime ensemble artifacts with the overhead floor mechanism (56.2% mean E2E with trace replay, 9.5% mean ITL).\n    11→\n    12→**Key insight:** Per-step MAPE is a poor proxy for E2E error (Round 2: 64.4% step → 427.8% E2E). This idea optimizes E2E *directly* rather than using step accuracy as an intermediate.\n    13→\n    14→## 2. Sub-Hypothesis Results Table\n    15→\n    16→| Sub-Hypothesis | Status | Key Metric | Takeaway |\n    17→|---|---|---|---|\n    18→| **H1:** CMA-ES + trace replay → < 15% E2E | **PARTIALLY SUPPORTED** | E2E 15.1% (target < 15%) | 3.7x improvement; 4/10 < 10%; narrowly missed target |\n    19→| **H2:** Workload-spec mode → < 50% E2E | **NOT TESTED** | All BLIS runs failed | Profile file mismatch between repos; infrastructure gap |\n    20→| **H3:** Additive corrections → -5pp E2E | **REFUTED for E2E** | E2E 17.2% (+2.1pp worse) | Corrections conflict with CMA-ES absorption; TTFT improved to 9.4% |\n    21→\n    22→## 3. Best BLIS E2E Result — Full Per-Experiment Error Table\n    23→\n    24→**H1 results (CMA-ES + trace replay):**\n    25→\n    26→| Experiment | Model | Workload | GT E2E (ms) | BLIS E2E (ms) | E2E Error | TTFT Error | ITL Error |\n    27→|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n    28→| llama-2-7b-tp1-roleplay | llama-2-7b | roleplay | 2,071 | 1,612 | 22.2% | 60.8% | 91.1% |\n    29→| llama-2-70b-tp4-general | llama-2-70b | general | 5,321 | 4,458 | 16.2% | 82.5% | 72.0% |\n    30→| llama-2-70b-hf-tp4-codegen | llama-2-70b-hf | codegen | 4,606 | 4,432 | **3.8%** | 67.6% | 111.6% |\n    31→| llama-2-70b-tp4-roleplay | llama-2-70b | roleplay | 4,562 | 4,249 | **6.9%** | 67.6% | 117.0% |\n    32→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-codegen | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | codegen | 4,675 | 3,229 | 30.9% | 66.4% | 41.5% |\n    33→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-general | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | general | 5,039 | 4,399 | 12.7% | 57.3% | 78.1% |\n    34→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1-tp2-roleplay | mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | roleplay | 4,685 | 3,084 | 34.2% | 69.3% | 34.5% |\n    35→| codellama-34b-tp2-general | codellama-34b | general | 4,093 | 4,044 | **1.2%** | 69.3% | 102.7% |\n    36→| codellama-34b-tp2-codegen | codellama-34b | codegen | 3,723 | 3,536 | **5.0%** | 68.9% | 90.2% |\n    37→| codellama-34b-tp2-roleplay | codellama-34b | roleplay | 3,670 | 3,028 | 17.5% | 66.2% | 135.4% |\n    38→| **MEAN** | | | | | **15.1%** | **67.6%** | **87.4%** |\n    39→\n    40→**Best per-model CMA-ES results (optimization across workloads):**\n    41→\n    42→| Model | Initial E2E | Optimized E2E | Improvement |\n    43→|---|---|---|---|\n    44→| llama-2-7b | 60.9% | 22.2% | 2.7x |\n    45→| llama-2-70b | 58.2% avg | **8.3%** | 7.0x |\n    46→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | 53.0% avg | 25.9% | 2.0x |\n    47→| codellama-34b | 55.8% avg | **7.9%** | 7.1x |\n    48→\n    49→## 4. What Worked (Specific Techniques)\n    50→\n    51→1. **CMA-ES for black-box DES calibration** — Treating BLIS as a black-box function and optimizing against E2E directly was effective. CMA-ES found parameter settings that reduce E2E error 2-7x per model, despite noisy multi-experiment objectives and ~20 parameters.\n    52→\n    53→2. **Per-model optimization** — Mandatory. Each model has fundamentally different step-time characteristics (7B: 3.9ms overhead, Mixtral: 9.1ms overhead). A single global optimization would fail.\n    54→\n    55→3. **Overhead floor as the primary knob** — The step_overhead_us parameter (overhead floor) controls the dominant timing characteristic. CMA-ES consistently tuned this upward (e.g., llama-2-7b: 3,897 → 5,051μs, +30%) to match real vLLM step cycle times.\n    56→\n    57→4. **Scheduling time as secondary knob** — For larger models (llama-2-70b), scheduling_processing_time_us doubled (415 → 821μs), capturing CPU overhead that the step-time model misses.\n    58→\n    59→5. **TTFT additive corrections (H3)** — While not helpful for E2E, applying per-model additive corrections to QueueingTime reduced TTFT error from 67.6% → 9.4%. This is the first time TTFT has been below 10% in this research.\n    60→\n    61→## 5. What Failed and Why (Root Causes)\n    62→\n    63→1. **E2E optimization sacrifices ITL accuracy** — CMA-ES optimizes the E2E objective, which can increase per-token overhead (output_token_processing_time_us) to match total E2E at the expense of ITL accuracy. ITL worsened from 9.5% → 87.4%. This is the fundamental tension: E2E = TTFT + Σ(ITL), so optimizing total while ignoring components produces imbalanced solutions.\n    64→\n    65→2. **Mixtral and llama-2-7b resist optimization** — These models achieved only 25.9% and 22.2% E2E respectively, vs. 8.3% and 7.9% for the others. Root causes:\n    66→   - **llama-2-7b:** Only 1 experiment (roleplay). CMA-ES has no cross-workload validation and may overfit.\n    67→   - **Mixtral:** MoE architecture has higher per-step variance and less predictable batch behavior.\n    68→\n    69→3. **H2 (workload-spec mode) completely failed** — Profile file mismatch between BLIS-research and inference-sim repos. The experiment directory naming conventions differ, preventing automatic matching.\n    70→\n    71→4. **H3 corrections conflict with H1 optimization** — CMA-ES already \"absorbed\" the TTFT deficit into its coefficient values. Applying post-hoc TTFT corrections double-counts the adjustment, worsening E2E by 2.1pp.\n    72→\n    73→## 6. Binding Constraints\n    74→\n    75→| Constraint | Status | Evidence |\n    76→|---|---|---|\n    77→| **BC-1: TTFT/simulation fidelity mismatch** | Partially resolved by H3 | TTFT 9.4% with corrections; 67.6% without |\n    78→| **BC-NEW: E2E ↔ ITL tradeoff** | **NEW BINDING CONSTRAINT** | Optimizing E2E worsens ITL (9.5% → 87.4%). Cannot optimize both with the same coefficient set. |\n    79→| **BC-2: KV feature scaling** | Not addressed | KV features are in the artifact but CMA-ES doesn't specifically target them |\n    80→| **BC-3: CodeLlama-34B anomaly** | Resolved | E2E 7.9% mean — CMA-ES found good coefficients for this model |\n    81→| **BC-4: Mixtral MoE variance** | Partially addressed | 25.9% mean — better than baseline but above target |\n    82→\n    83→## 7. Data Insights Discovered\n    84→\n    85→1. **E2E and ITL are in tension.** The LatencyModel interface has 5 methods that all contribute to E2E, but their contributions are nonlinearly coupled through simulation dynamics (queueing, batch formation). Optimizing total E2E via coefficient tuning can achieve good E2E by offsetting errors across methods — but this produces arbitrarily bad per-method metrics.\n    86→\n    87→2. **CMA-ES convergence is model-dependent.** Larger models (70B, 34B) converge faster to low E2E because they have more experiments (3 each) providing a smoother objective landscape. llama-2-7b (1 experiment) converges slowly and to a worse optimum.\n    88→\n    89→3. **The overhead floor works bidirectionally.** CMA-ES sometimes *decreased* step_overhead_us (codellama-34b: 6,673 → 5,998, -10%) while increasing scheduling time. This suggests the initial overhead floor was already close to optimal for some models, and the remaining error is in secondary method timing.\n    90→\n    91→4. **TTFT bias is systematic and model-independent.** All models under-predict TTFT by 3-4x (60-83% error). This is a simulation-level characteristic, not a step-time model issue. The additive correction (16-61ms per model) fully compensates.\n    92→\n    93→5. **Output token processing time is the hidden parameter.** CMA-ES increased output_token_processing_time_us dramatically for llama-2-7b (0 → 1,899μs). This effectively adds ~1.9ms per output token, which is physically implausible but mathematically optimal for E2E. This reveals that the LatencyModel interface lacks a \"simulation overhead\" parameter — the optimizer uses OutputTokenProcessingTime as a proxy for missing dynamics.\n    94→\n    95→## 8. Comparison to Baseline\n    96→\n    97→| Metric | R2 Workload-Spec | R3 Idea 1 (Trace) | R3 Idea 3 H1 (CMA-ES) | R3 Idea 3 H3 (Corrections) |\n    98→|---|---|---|---|---|\n    99→| Mean E2E error | 427.8% | 56.2% | **15.1%** | 17.2% |\n   100→| Mean TTFT error | 31,906% | 78.8% | 67.6% | **9.4%** |\n   101→| Mean ITL error | 33.6% | **9.5%** | 87.4% | 81.1% |\n   102→| E2E < 10% | 1/10 | 0/10 | **4/10** | 4/10 |\n   103→| E2E < 15% | — | 0/10 | **5/10** | 4/10 |\n   104→\n   105→**Net assessment:** CMA-ES E2E optimization achieves the best E2E accuracy in the research program (15.1% mean, 4/10 < 10%). However, it sacrifices ITL accuracy and TTFT accuracy to achieve this. The combination of H1 (E2E optimization) + H3 (TTFT correction) produces the most balanced result: 17.2% E2E + 9.4% TTFT, but ITL remains at 81.1%.\n   106→\n   107→## 9. Go Integration Feasibility\n   108→\n   109→**Already integrated.** The Go changes needed for this experiment were:\n   110→\n   111→| File | Change | Lines |\n   112→|---|---|---|\n   113→| `sim/config.go` | Added `StepMLModelPath` field + `WithStepMLModel` builder | ~12 |\n   114→| `sim/latency/latency.go` | Added StepML dispatch in factory (after roofline, before blackbox) | ~7 |\n   115→| `cmd/root.go` | Added `--stepml-model` CLI flag + wiring | ~8 |\n   116→\n   117→Total: ~27 lines of Go changes. The optimized artifacts use the same JSON schema as the Round 2 artifacts and load through the existing `sim/latency/stepml.go` evaluator unchanged.\n   118→\n   119→**Artifact format:** Standard StepML JSON with version 2, step_time_regimes, and calibrated overhead/secondary method values. No new fields needed.\n   120→\n   121→**Performance:** Each BLIS simulation run with StepML takes 2-10 seconds (depending on experiment size). The CMA-ES optimization requires 96-152 evaluations per model, totaling ~30 minutes per model.\n   122→\n   123→## 10. Generalization Results\n   124→\n   125→### H4: Leave-One-Workload-Out (LOWO) — Part A Per-Workload Breakdown\n   126→\n   127→**Status: PARTIALLY SUPPORTED**\n   128→\n   129→CMA-ES-optimized artifacts evaluated per-workload:\n   130→\n   131→| Model Group | Codegen | General | Roleplay | Range (pp) | Mean |\n   132→|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n   133→| llama-2-7b | — | — | 22.2% | — | 22.2% |\n   134→| llama-2-70b | **3.8%** | 16.2% | **6.9%** | 12.4 | 9.0% |\n   135→| codellama-34b | **5.0%** | **1.2%** | 17.5% | 16.3 | 7.9% |\n   136→| mixtral-8x7b-v0-1 | 30.9% | 12.7% | 34.2% | 21.5 | 25.9% |\n   137→\n   138→Dense models generalize well across workloads (9-16pp range). Mixtral shows highest workload variance (21.5pp). 8/10 experiments within 2x of aggregate (15.1%), but mixtral-roleplay (34.2%) slightly exceeds. Part B (LOWO CMA-ES re-optimization) not tested (requires ~4.5 hours of CMA-ES runs).\n   139→\n   140→### H5: Leave-One-Model-Out (LOMO) — Cross-Model Artifact Transfer\n   141→\n   142→**Status: SUPPORTED** — Mean best-donor E2E = **14.8%** (threshold <50%)\n   143→\n   144→Cross-model transfer matrix (E2E %):\n   145→\n   146→| Donor → Target | codellama-34b | llama-2-70b | llama-2-7b | mixtral-8x7b |\n   147→|---|---|---|---|---|\n   148→| codellama-34b | — | 21.2% | 24.3% | 21.2% |\n   149→| llama-2-70b | 24.7% | — | 94.0% | **5.1%** |\n   150→| llama-2-7b | 40.4% | 53.8% | — | 53.8% |\n   151→| mixtral-8x7b | **11.9%** | 26.0% | **20.9%** | — |\n   152→\n   153→**Best donor per target:**\n   154→- codellama-34b ← mixtral (11.9%)\n   155→- llama-2-70b ← codellama-34b (21.2%)\n   156→- llama-2-7b ← mixtral (20.9%)\n   157→- mixtral ← llama-2-70b (**5.1%**)\n   158→\n   159→**Key insight:** CMA-ES artifacts have dramatically better cross-model transfer than per-step models because they capture simulation-level dynamics (overhead floor, scheduling overhead) that are partially model-independent. Mixtral is the best universal donor; 70B→Mixtral transfer (5.1%) actually outperforms Mixtral's own in-distribution result (25.9%).\n   160→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017vgie1jSaXiJSc9cebn2B7","session_id":"6c146fd0-2769-4d18-b481-0819d4602c26","uuid":"99a234ea-6405-46f6-b804-679a2d5e7284"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SBwNRFrDasN4q7EPvQA8d6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Idea 3: End-to-End Calibration via Direct E2E Objective\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→Jointly calibrate all LatencyModel coefficients by directly minimizing BLIS E2E mean error using black-box optimization, bypassing per-component accuracy entirely. Attacks all binding constraints by optimizing the metric that matters (E2E error) rather than intermediate metrics (per-step MAPE).\n     6→\n     7→**LatencyModel methods covered:** All 5: StepTime (calibrated coefficients), QueueingTime (calibrated), OutputTokenProcessingTime (calibrated), SchedulingProcessingTime (calibrated), PreemptionProcessingTime (calibrated).\n     8→\n     9→**Go integration path:** Coefficient export — calibrated values written to the same StepML artifact JSON format. No new Go code.\n    10→\n    11→## Prior Round Context\n    12→\n    13→- **Round 2 (Idea 1, H2):** Joint Bayesian optimization was **never run** because the base model (87.4% per-step MAPE) was too inaccurate. This blocked the whole idea.\n    14→- **Round 2 (Idea 2, H3):** Secondary method calibration contributed **0.0pp** improvement — 200-400us corrections invisible against 100%+ errors.\n    15→- **Round 2 key finding:** Per-step MAPE is a poor proxy for E2E error. 64.4% per-step → 427.8% E2E but 33.6% ITL. The relationship is nonlinear and mediated by simulation dynamics.\n    16→- **Literature:** AIConfigurator [arXiv 2601.06288] uses \"empirical correction factors\" calibrated against E2E for 3.35% TTFT error. Block [arXiv 2508.03611] uses \"online calibration\" with simple additive corrections (\"+10 steps\"). Trace-driven DES calibration is standard practice: calibrate against metrics you care about, not intermediates.\n    17→- **Key difference from Round 2:** We now have a **much better starting point** — Round 2's best model produces 33.6% mean ITL (5/10 < 10%) with the overhead floor. Round 2's BO attempt started from 87.4% per-step MAPE (too poor for calibration).\n    18→\n    19→## Training Strategy\n    20→\n    21→Per-model optimization (mandatory). Each model's coefficients optimized independently. Cross-workload validation: optimize on 2 workloads, validate on the held-out 3rd. Uses CMA-ES (Covariance Matrix Adaptation Evolution Strategy) for derivative-free optimization.\n    22→\n    23→**Data split:** Hold-one-workload-out cross-validation. For each model: train on 2 workloads, validate on 1. Rotate to get 3 folds.\n    24→\n    25→---\n    26→\n    27→## Sub-Hypothesis H1: Trace Replay + E2E Optimization Baseline\n    28→\n    29→### Claim\n    30→\n    31→Starting from Round 2's best coefficients, CMA-ES optimization of StepML artifact parameters against BLIS E2E mean error (using trace replay from Idea 1) achieves < 15% mean E2E error across all experiments.\n    32→\n    33→### Rationale\n    34→\n    35→This hypothesis combines Idea 1's trace replay (eliminating workload-spec error) with direct E2E optimization. By removing the workload-spec mismatch and optimizing directly against E2E, we attack both the PRIMARY (BC-1) and SECONDARY (BC-2, BC-3) binding constraints simultaneously. The starting point (33.6% mean ITL with overhead floor) is close enough to the target that derivative-free optimization should converge.\n    36→\n    37→The parameter space is small enough for CMA-ES: per model, we optimize ~8–12 parameters (step_time regime coefficients, overhead, secondary method constants). With 10 experiments × 3 workloads per model, each evaluation takes ~5 seconds (BLIS run). Budget: 200 evaluations per model × 4 models = ~67 minutes total.\n    38→\n    39→### Method\n    40→\n    41→1. **Setup:** Generate trace replay files for all experiments (from Idea 1). Define the objective: `f(params) = mean_i |BLIS_E2E_i(params) - GT_E2E_i| / GT_E2E_i` where i indexes experiments for this model\n    42→2. **Parameter vector:** For each model: [regime coefficients (decode intercept, decode slopes, mixed intercept, mixed slopes), step_overhead_us, step_overhead_per_req_us, queueing_time_intercept, queueing_time_slope, output_token_processing_time_us, scheduling_processing_time_us, preemption_processing_time_us]\n    43→3. **Initial point:** Round 2's best coefficients per model\n    44→4. **Bounds:** Each parameter bounded to [0.1× initial, 10× initial] (or [0, 10× initial] for non-negative params). Overhead floor always >= 1000us.\n    45→5. **Optimize with CMA-ES:** sigma0 = 0.3 × initial values, population size 10, budget 200 evaluations per model\n    46→6. **Evaluate:** Full per-experiment E2E/TTFT/ITL error table with optimized coefficients\n    47→\n    48→### Refutation Criteria\n    49→\n    50→- **Supported:** Mean E2E error < 15% with trace replay. At least 5/10 experiments < 10%.\n    51→- **Refuted:** Mean E2E error > 30% even with trace replay + optimization — BLIS scheduling divergence is too large for coefficient tuning to overcome.\n    52→\n    53→### Diagnostics\n    54→\n    55→- Convergence plot: E2E error vs evaluation count per model\n    56→- Optimized vs initial coefficient values (identify which parameters moved most)\n    57→- Per-experiment E2E/TTFT/ITL error before and after optimization\n    58→- Sensitivity analysis: which parameters have largest marginal impact on E2E\n    59→\n    60→---\n    61→\n    62→## Sub-Hypothesis H2: Workload-Spec Mode E2E Optimization\n    63→\n    64→### Claim\n    65→\n    66→CMA-ES optimization in workload-spec mode (not trace replay) achieves < 50% mean E2E error, a 8.5× improvement over Round 2's 427.8%.\n    67→\n    68→### Rationale\n    69→\n    70→Even without trace replay, E2E optimization might partially compensate for workload-spec mismatch by finding coefficients that produce the correct *mean* E2E despite incorrect intermediate behavior (arrival patterns, TTFT). The optimizer can effectively \"absorb\" workload-spec errors into the coefficient values. This is useful because: (a) trace replay requires ground-truth data, while workload specs are always available; (b) if the optimizer can partially compensate, it provides a practical deployment path.\n    71→\n    72→However, we expect this to be less effective than H1 because the optimizer cannot correct for exponentially divergent TTFT from workload-spec arrival rate mismatch (per DistServe's M/D/1 model).\n    73→\n    74→### Method\n    75→\n    76→1. Same CMA-ES setup as H1, but using workload-spec mode (inference-perf profiles from Round 2)\n    77→2. Objective: `f(params) = mean_i |BLIS_E2E_i(params) - GT_E2E_i| / GT_E2E_i` with workload-spec BLIS runs\n    78→3. Same parameter vector and bounds as H1\n    79→4. Budget: 200 evaluations per model\n    80→5. Cross-validate: optimize on 2 workloads, validate on the held-out 3rd\n    81→\n    82→### Refutation Criteria\n    83→\n    84→- **Supported:** Mean E2E error < 50% with workload-spec mode (8.5× improvement over 427.8%).\n    85→- **Refuted:** Mean E2E error > 200% — E2E optimization cannot compensate for workload-spec mismatch.\n    86→\n    87→### Diagnostics\n    88→\n    89→- Comparison: H1 (trace replay) vs H2 (workload spec) per experiment\n    90→- Cross-validation results: do optimized coefficients generalize to held-out workloads?\n    91→- Coefficient drift analysis: how much do coefficients change from the initial point? Large drift suggests overfitting to workload-spec artifacts.\n    92→\n    93→---\n    94→\n    95→## Sub-Hypothesis H3: Additive Correction Factors\n    96→\n    97→### Claim\n    98→\n    99→Simple additive or multiplicative correction factors applied to TTFT and ITL (calibrated from trace replay results) close at least 5pp of remaining E2E error beyond what H1 achieves.\n   100→\n   101→### Rationale\n   102→\n   103→AIConfigurator uses \"empirical correction factors modeled as piecewise linear functions\" for TTFT, achieving 3.35% error. Block uses \"+10 steps\" as a simple additive correction. Even if BLIS's scheduling differs from vLLM in systematic ways (e.g., consistently scheduling prefills one step later), a simple correction factor can compensate.\n   104→\n   105→The correction approach is: `corrected_TTFT = TTFT_BLIS × alpha_ttft + beta_ttft`, where alpha_ttft and beta_ttft are calibrated per model. Similarly for ITL. These corrections are applied as part of the LatencyModel's QueueingTime and OutputTokenProcessingTime methods.\n   106→\n   107→### Method\n   108→\n   109→1. From H1 results, compute per-experiment TTFT and ITL residuals: `residual = BLIS_metric - GT_metric`\n   110→2. Fit linear correction models per model: `corrected = alpha * predicted + beta`\n   111→3. Implement corrections as adjustments to QueueingTime (for TTFT) and OutputTokenProcessingTime (for ITL)\n   112→4. Re-run BLIS with corrected LatencyModel\n   113→5. Measure improvement over H1's uncorrected results\n   114→\n   115→### Refutation Criteria\n   116→\n   117→- **Supported:** Corrections reduce mean E2E error by at least 5pp vs H1's baseline.\n   118→- **Refuted:** Corrections reduce mean E2E error by < 2pp — systematic bias is not the dominant residual, and remaining error is stochastic/per-request variance.\n   119→\n   120→### Diagnostics\n   121→\n   122→- TTFT and ITL residual distributions per model (are they systematic or random?)\n   123→- Correction factor values (alpha, beta) per model\n   124→- Pre- and post-correction per-experiment E2E/TTFT/ITL errors\n   125→- Scatter plot: BLIS-predicted vs ground-truth TTFT and ITL\n   126→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017vgie1jSaXiJSc9cebn2B7","session_id":"6c146fd0-2769-4d18-b481-0819d4602c26","uuid":"c007a5a0-6e5e-4611-959c-b43976b82983"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QwRrtJR3dPQhgQo31B8Zyn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2→\"\"\"Round 4, Idea 1: Multi-Objective Constrained CMA-ES with ITL Penalty.\n     3→\n     4→Implements all 4 sub-hypotheses:\n     5→  H1: Constrained CMA-ES with dual E2E+ITL objective\n     6→  H2: Pareto sweep across alpha values\n     7→  H3: LOMO (leave-one-model-out) generalization\n     8→  H4: LOWO (leave-one-workload-out) generalization\n     9→\n    10→Uses the shared infrastructure from hypotheses/h-stepml/shared/ for data loading,\n    11→BLIS validation, and evaluation.\n    12→\"\"\"\n    13→\n    14→import copy\n    15→import json\n    16→import os\n    17→import re\n    18→import subprocess\n    19→import sys\n    20→import tempfile\n    21→import time\n    22→\n    23→import numpy as np\n    24→\n    25→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    26→# Paths\n    27→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    28→_SCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\n    29→_SHARED_DIR = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"shared\"))\n    30→_REPO_ROOT = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"..\", \"..\"))\n    31→# Ground truth lives in the main BLIS-research repo (not the worktree)\n    32→# Worktree root is stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-1-constrained-cmaes/\n    33→# BLIS-research is at inference-sim-package/BLIS-research/\n    34→_INFERENCE_SIM_PKG = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(_REPO_ROOT, \"..\", \"..\"))\n    35→_DATA_ROOT = os.path.join(_INFERENCE_SIM_PKG, \"BLIS-research\", \"eval\", \"ground_truth\")\n    36→_R3_ARTIFACTS_DIR = os.path.join(\n    37→    _INFERENCE_SIM_PKG, \"BLIS-research\", \"hypotheses\", \"h-stepml\",\n    38→    \"round3\", \"idea-3-e2e-calibration\", \"h1-trace-e2e-opt\", \"artifacts\"\n    39→)\n    40→BINARY_PATH = os.path.join(_REPO_ROOT, \"simulation_worker\")\n    41→BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS = 16\n    42→\n    43→sys.path.insert(0, _SHARED_DIR)\n    44→\n    45→import yaml\n    46→from convert_lifecycle_to_traces import convert_experiment\n    47→from validate_blis import (\n    48→    extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n    49→    extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log,\n    50→    load_exp_config,\n    51→    load_ground_truth_metrics,\n    52→    parse_blis_stdout,\n    53→    parse_experiment_dir,\n    54→)\n    55→\n    56→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    57→# TTFT corrections from R3 H3 (per-model additive corrections in ms)\n    58→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    59→TTFT_CORRECTIONS_MS = {\n    60→    \"llama-2-7b\": 16.49,\n    61→    \"llama-2-70b\": 60.98,\n    62→    \"llama-2-70b-hf\": 37.57,\n    63→    \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\": 40.16,\n    64→    \"codellama-34b\": 32.48,\n    65→}\n    66→\n    67→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    68→# Model group mapping (experiment dir model name -> group)\n    69→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    70→# For CMA-ES optimization, group experiments by shared optimizer.\n    71→# 70b and 70b-hf share the same optimizer (both are 70B models).\n    72→# Each experiment's specific artifact is loaded from R3 by exact model name.\n    73→MODEL_GROUPS = {\n    74→    \"llama-2-7b\": \"llama-2-7b\",\n    75→    \"llama-2-70b\": \"llama-2-70b\",\n    76→    \"llama-2-70b-hf\": \"llama-2-70b\",  # Same optimization group as 70b\n    77→    \"codellama-34b\": \"codellama-34b\",\n    78→    \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\": \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\",\n    79→}\n    80→\n    81→# For LOMO, we group 70b and 70b-hf as one model\n    82→LOMO_MODEL_GROUPS = {\n    83→    \"llama-2-7b\": \"llama-2-7b\",\n    84→    \"llama-2-70b\": \"llama-2-70b\",\n    85→    \"llama-2-70b-hf\": \"llama-2-70b\",\n    86→    \"codellama-34b\": \"codellama-34b\",\n    87→    \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\": \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\",\n    88→}\n    89→\n    90→\n    91→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    92→# Experiment discovery\n    93→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    94→def discover_experiments():\n    95→    \"\"\"Discover all valid experiments in the ground truth directory.\"\"\"\n    96→    experiments = []\n    97→    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(_DATA_ROOT)):\n    98→        dirpath = os.path.join(_DATA_ROOT, dirname)\n    99→        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n   100→            continue\n   101→        summary_path = os.path.join(dirpath, \"results\", \"summary_lifecycle_metrics.json\")\n   102→        if not os.path.isfile(summary_path):\n   103→            continue\n   104→\n   105→        meta = parse_experiment_dir(dirname)\n   106→        gt = load_ground_truth_metrics(dirpath)\n   107→        exp_config = load_exp_config(dirpath)\n   108→        kv_blocks = extract_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n   109→        cpu_kv_blocks = extract_cpu_kv_blocks_from_vllm_log(dirpath)\n   110→\n   111→        if kv_blocks is None:\n   112→            continue\n   113→\n   114→        model_group = MODEL_GROUPS.get(meta[\"model\"], meta[\"model\"])\n   115→\n   116→        experiments.append({\n   117→            \"dirname\": dirname,\n   118→            \"dirpath\": dirpath,\n   119→            \"model\": meta[\"model\"],\n   120→            \"model_group\": model_group,\n   121→            \"workload\": meta[\"workload\"],\n   122→            \"tp\": meta[\"tp\"],\n   123→            \"gt\": gt,\n   124→            \"exp_config\": exp_config,\n   125→            \"kv_blocks\": kv_blocks,\n   126→            \"cpu_kv_blocks\": cpu_kv_blocks,\n   127→        })\n   128→\n   129→    return experiments\n   130→\n   131→\n   132→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   133→# Trace CSV generation (cached)\n   134→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   135→_TRACE_CACHE = {}\n   136→\n   137→\n   138→def get_trace_csv(exp):\n   139→    \"\"\"Get or create trace CSV for an experiment.\"\"\"\n   140→    dirname = exp[\"dirname\"]\n   141→    if dirname in _TRACE_CACHE:\n   142→        return _TRACE_CACHE[dirname]\n   143→\n   144→    trace_dir = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"traces\")\n   145→    csv_path = os.path.join(trace_dir, f\"{dirname}.csv\")\n   146→    if not os.path.isfile(csv_path):\n   147→        csv_path = convert_experiment(exp[\"dirpath\"], trace_dir)\n   148→\n   149→    _TRACE_CACHE[dirname] = csv_path\n   150→    return csv_path\n   151→\n   152→\n   153→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   154→# BLIS execution (trace replay mode)\n   155→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   156→def run_blis_trace(trace_csv, exp_config, kv_blocks, artifact_path, horizon_us,\n   157→                   cpu_kv_blocks=0):\n   158→    \"\"\"Run BLIS in trace replay mode with a StepML artifact.\"\"\"\n   159→    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix=\".json\", delete=False) as f:\n   160→        results_path = f.name\n   161→\n   162→    cmd = [\n   163→        BINARY_PATH, \"run\",\n   164→        \"--model\", exp_config.get(\"model\", \"unknown\"),\n   165→        \"--workload\", \"traces\",\n   166→        \"--workload-traces-filepath\", trace_csv,\n   167→        \"--tp\", str(exp_config.get(\"tensor_parallelism\", 1)),\n   168→        \"--max-model-len\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_model_len\", 4096)),\n   169→        \"--max-num-running-reqs\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_seqs\", 128)),\n   170→        \"--max-num-scheduled-tokens\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_batched_tokens\", 2048)),\n   171→        \"--total-kv-blocks\", str(kv_blocks),\n   172→        \"--block-size-in-tokens\", str(BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS),\n   173→        \"--horizon\", str(horizon_us),\n   174→        \"--alpha-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   175→        \"--beta-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   176→        \"--stepml-model\", artifact_path,\n   177→        \"--results-path\", results_path,\n   178→        \"--log\", \"error\",\n   179→    ]\n   180→    if cpu_kv_blocks > 0:\n   181→        cmd.extend([\"--kv-cpu-blocks\", str(cpu_kv_blocks)])\n   182→\n   183→    try:\n   184→        result = subprocess.run(\n   185→            cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=300,\n   186→            cwd=os.path.dirname(BINARY_PATH),\n   187→        )\n   188→    except (subprocess.TimeoutExpired, FileNotFoundError):\n   189→        return None\n   190→    finally:\n   191→        if os.path.exists(results_path):\n   192→            os.unlink(results_path)\n   193→\n   194→    if result.returncode != 0:\n   195→        return None\n   196→    return parse_blis_stdout(result.stdout)\n   197→\n   198→\n   199→def compute_error(predicted, observed):\n   200→    \"\"\"Compute relative error: |predicted - observed| / observed.\"\"\"\n   201→    if observed == 0:\n   202→        return float(\"inf\") if predicted != 0 else 0.0\n   203→    return abs(predicted - observed) / observed\n   204→\n   205→\n   206→def compute_horizon(exp):\n   207→    \"\"\"Compute a horizon that covers all requests.\"\"\"\n   208→    gt = exp[\"gt\"]\n   209→    e2e_s = gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"]\n   210→    n_requests = gt[\"num_requests\"]\n   211→    rps = gt[\"throughput_rps\"]\n   212→    if rps > 0:\n   213→        duration_s = n_requests / rps\n   214→    else:\n   215→        duration_s = 600\n   216→    return int((duration_s + e2e_s * 3 + 120) * 1_000_000)\n   217→\n   218→\n   219→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   220→# Artifact manipulation\n   221→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   222→def load_r3_artifact(model_group):\n   223→    \"\"\"Load the R3 CMA-ES optimized artifact for a model group.\n   224→\n   225→    For the llama-2-70b group, loads the 70b artifact (not 70b-hf).\n   226→    \"\"\"\n   227→    filename = f\"{model_group}_optimized.json\"\n   228→    path = os.path.join(_R3_ARTIFACTS_DIR, filename)\n   229→    if not os.path.isfile(path):\n   230→        # Try without -hf suffix\n   231→        alt = f\"{model_group.replace('-hf', '')}_optimized.json\"\n   232→        alt_path = os.path.join(_R3_ARTIFACTS_DIR, alt)\n   233→        if os.path.isfile(alt_path):\n   234→            path = alt_path\n   235→        else:\n   236→            raise FileNotFoundError(f\"R3 artifact not found: {path}\")\n   237→    with open(path) as f:\n   238→        return json.load(f)\n   239→\n   240→\n   241→def artifact_to_param_vector(artifact):\n   242→    \"\"\"Extract optimizable parameters from a StepML artifact.\"\"\"\n   243→    params = {}\n   244→    params[\"step_overhead_us\"] = artifact.get(\"step_overhead_us\", 4000)\n   245→    params[\"step_overhead_per_req_us\"] = artifact.get(\"step_overhead_per_req_us\", 0)\n   246→    params[\"output_token_processing_time_us\"] = artifact.get(\"output_token_processing_time_us\", 0)\n   247→    params[\"scheduling_processing_time_us\"] = artifact.get(\"scheduling_processing_time_us\", 0)\n   248→    params[\"preemption_processing_time_us\"] = artifact.get(\"preemption_processing_time_us\", 0)\n   249→\n   250→    qt = artifact.get(\"queueing_time\")\n   251→    if qt:\n   252→        params[\"queueing_intercept\"] = qt.get(\"intercept\", 0)\n   253→\n   254→    for regime in artifact.get(\"step_time_regimes\", []):\n   255→        prefix = regime[\"name\"]\n   256→        model = regime[\"model\"]\n   257→        params[f\"{prefix}_intercept\"] = model.get(\"intercept\", 0)\n   258→        for feat, coeff in model.get(\"feature_coefficients\", {}).items():\n   259→            params[f\"{prefix}_{feat}\"] = coeff\n   260→\n   261→    return params\n   262→\n   263→\n   264→def param_vector_to_artifact(params, base_artifact):\n   265→    \"\"\"Reconstruct a StepML artifact from optimized parameters.\"\"\"\n   266→    art = copy.deepcopy(base_artifact)\n   267→    art[\"step_overhead_us\"] = params[\"step_overhead_us\"]\n   268→    art[\"step_overhead_per_req_us\"] = params.get(\"step_overhead_per_req_us\", 0)\n   269→    art[\"output_token_processing_time_us\"] = params[\"output_token_processing_time_us\"]\n   270→    art[\"scheduling_processing_time_us\"] = params[\"scheduling_processing_time_us\"]\n   271→    art[\"preemption_processing_time_us\"] = params[\"preemption_processing_time_us\"]\n   272→\n   273→    if \"queueing_intercept\" in params:\n   274→        if art.get(\"queueing_time\") is None:\n   275→            art[\"queueing_time\"] = {\n   276→                \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   277→                \"intercept\": 0,\n   278→                \"feature_coefficients\": {},\n   279→            }\n   280→        art[\"queueing_time\"][\"intercept\"] = params[\"queueing_intercept\"]\n   281→\n   282→    for regime in art.get(\"step_time_regimes\", []):\n   283→        prefix = regime[\"name\"]\n   284→        key = f\"{prefix}_intercept\"\n   285→        if key in params:\n   286→            regime[\"model\"][\"intercept\"] = params[key]\n   287→        for feat in list(regime[\"model\"].get(\"feature_coefficients\", {}).keys()):\n   288→            key = f\"{prefix}_{feat}\"\n   289→            if key in params:\n   290→                regime[\"model\"][\"feature_coefficients\"][feat] = params[key]\n   291→\n   292→    return art\n   293→\n   294→\n   295→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   296→# Constrained parameter bounds (the key R4 innovation)\n   297→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   298→def compute_bounds(params, base_overhead):\n   299→    \"\"\"Compute constrained parameter bounds.\n   300→\n   301→    Key constraints vs R3:\n   302→    - output_token_processing_time_us: [0, 500] (was [0, 5000+])\n   303→    - scheduling_processing_time_us: [0, 2000] (was unbounded)\n   304→    - step_overhead_us: [base*0.8, base*3.0] (was [base*0.3, base*5.0])\n   305→    - Regime coefficients: tighter bounds (+/- 2x instead of +/- 5x)\n   306→    \"\"\"\n   307→    lower = {}\n   308→    upper = {}\n   309→\n   310→    for name, val in params.items():\n   311→        if name == \"output_token_processing_time_us\":\n   312→            lower[name] = 0\n   313→            upper[name] = 500  # Hard cap (was up to 5000+ in R3)\n   314→        elif name == \"scheduling_processing_time_us\":\n   315→            lower[name] = 0\n   316→            upper[name] = 2000\n   317→        elif name == \"preemption_processing_time_us\":\n   318→            lower[name] = 0\n   319→            upper[name] = 1000\n   320→        elif name == \"step_overhead_us\":\n   321→            lower[name] = max(1000, base_overhead * 0.8)\n   322→            upper[name] = base_overhead * 3.0\n   323→        elif name == \"step_overhead_per_req_us\":\n   324→            lower[name] = 0\n   325→            upper[name] = max(200, abs(val) * 3)\n   326→        elif name == \"queueing_intercept\":\n   327→            lower[name] = -1000\n   328→            upper[name] = 2000\n   329→        elif \"intercept\" in name:\n   330→            lower[name] = val - abs(val) * 2 - 2000\n   331→            upper[name] = val + abs(val) * 2 + 2000\n   332→        else:\n   333→            # Regime coefficients: +/- 2x (tighter than R3's +/- 5x)\n   334→            lower[name] = val - abs(val) * 2 - 50\n   335→            upper[name] = val + abs(val) * 2 + 50\n   336→\n   337→    return lower, upper\n   338→\n   339→\n   340→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   341→# Constrained CMA-ES objective function\n   342→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   343→def evaluate_artifact(artifact, exps, ttft_correction_ms=0):\n   344→    \"\"\"Evaluate a StepML artifact across experiments.\n   345→\n   346→    Returns dict with per-experiment E2E, TTFT, ITL errors.\n   347→    \"\"\"\n   348→    # Write artifact to temp file\n   349→    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(\n   350→        mode=\"w\", suffix=\".json\", delete=False\n   351→    ) as f:\n   352→        json.dump(artifact, f)\n   353→        artifact_path = f.name\n   354→\n   355→    results = []\n   356→    try:\n   357→        for exp in exps:\n   358→            trace_csv = get_trace_csv(exp)\n   359→            horizon_us = compute_horizon(exp)\n   360→\n   361→            blis = run_blis_trace(\n   362→                trace_csv, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"],\n   363→                artifact_path, horizon_us, exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   364→            )\n   365→\n   366→            if blis is None:\n   367→                results.append({\n   368→                    \"experiment\": exp[\"dirname\"],\n   369→                    \"e2e_error\": 5.0,  # penalty\n   370→                    \"ttft_error\": 5.0,\n   371→                    \"itl_error\": 5.0,\n   372→                    \"status\": \"failed\",\n   373→                })\n   374→                continue\n   375→\n   376→            # Apply TTFT additive correction\n   377→            corrected_ttft = blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"] + ttft_correction_ms\n   378→\n   379→            gt = exp[\"gt\"]\n   380→            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   381→            ttft_err = compute_error(corrected_ttft, gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   382→            itl_err = compute_error(blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"], gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   383→\n   384→            results.append({\n   385→                \"experiment\": exp[\"dirname\"],\n   386→                \"model\": exp[\"model\"],\n   387→                \"workload\": exp[\"workload\"],\n   388→                \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n   389→                \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n   390→                \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n   391→                \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n   392→                \"blis_ttft_ms\": corrected_ttft,\n   393→                \"blis_itl_ms\": blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n   394→                \"gt_e2e_ms\": gt[\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   395→                \"gt_ttft_ms\": gt[\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   396→                \"gt_itl_ms\": gt[\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   397→                \"status\": \"ok\",\n   398→            })\n   399→    finally:\n   400→        os.unlink(artifact_path)\n   401→\n   402→    return results\n   403→\n   404→\n   405→def make_objective(base_artifact, param_names, exps, alpha, ttft_correction_ms):\n   406→    \"\"\"Create a CMA-ES objective function with dual E2E+ITL penalty.\n   407→\n   408→    objective = alpha * mean_e2e + (1-alpha) * mean_itl\n   409→              + 10 * max(0, mean_itl - 0.20)  # hard penalty for ITL > 20%\n   410→    \"\"\"\n   411→    eval_count = [0]\n   412→\n   413→    def objective(x):\n   414→        eval_count[0] += 1\n   415→        params = dict(zip(param_names, x))\n   416→        artifact = param_vector_to_artifact(params, base_artifact)\n   417→\n   418→        results = evaluate_artifact(artifact, exps, ttft_correction_ms)\n   419→        e2e_errors = [r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in results]\n   420→        itl_errors = [r[\"itl_error\"] for r in results]\n   421→\n   422→        mean_e2e = np.mean(e2e_errors)\n   423→        mean_itl = np.mean(itl_errors)\n   424→\n   425→        # Dual objective with ITL penalty\n   426→        obj = alpha * mean_e2e + (1 - alpha) * mean_itl\n   427→        # Penalty for ITL > 20%\n   428→        itl_penalty = 10.0 * max(0, mean_itl - 0.20)\n   429→        obj += itl_penalty\n   430→\n   431→        if eval_count[0] % 5 == 0 or eval_count[0] == 1:\n   432→            print(f\"  Eval {eval_count[0]:3d}: E2E={mean_e2e*100:.1f}% \"\n   433→                  f\"ITL={mean_itl*100:.1f}% obj={obj:.4f}\")\n   434→\n   435→        return obj\n   436→\n   437→    return objective, eval_count\n   438→\n   439→\n   440→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   441→# H1: Run constrained CMA-ES per model group\n   442→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   443→def run_h1(experiments, alpha=0.5, max_evals=100, output_dir=None):\n   444→    \"\"\"Run constrained CMA-ES per model group with dual E2E+ITL objective.\"\"\"\n   445→    import cma\n   446→\n   447→    if output_dir is None:\n   448→        output_dir = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"h1-constrained-cmaes\")\n   449→    os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)\n   450→    artifacts_dir = os.path.join(output_dir, \"artifacts\")\n   451→    os.makedirs(artifacts_dir, exist_ok=True)\n   452→\n   453→    # Group experiments by model\n   454→    model_exps = {}\n   455→    for exp in experiments:\n   456→        group = exp[\"model_group\"]\n   457→        model_exps.setdefault(group, []).append(exp)\n   458→\n   459→    all_results = []\n   460→    optimization_logs = {}\n   461→\n   462→    for model_group in sorted(model_exps.keys()):\n   463→        exps = model_exps[model_group]\n   464→        print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n   465→        print(f\"  Optimizing: {model_group} ({len(exps)} experiments)\")\n   466→        print(f\"  Alpha={alpha} (E2E weight)\")\n   467→        print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n   468→\n   469→        # Load R3 artifact as starting point\n   470→        r3_art = load_r3_artifact(model_group)\n   471→        params = artifact_to_param_vector(r3_art)\n   472→        param_names = sorted(params.keys())\n   473→        x0 = [params[n] for n in param_names]\n   474→\n   475→        # Get TTFT correction\n   476→        model_for_ttft = model_group\n   477→        if model_group == \"llama-2-70b\":\n   478→            model_for_ttft = \"llama-2-70b\"\n   479→        ttft_ms = TTFT_CORRECTIONS_MS.get(model_for_ttft, 0)\n   480→\n   481→        # Compute initial objective\n   482→        initial_results = evaluate_artifact(r3_art, exps, ttft_ms)\n   483→        initial_e2e = np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in initial_results])\n   484→        initial_itl = np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in initial_results])\n   485→        print(f\"  Initial: E2E={initial_e2e*100:.1f}% ITL={initial_itl*100:.1f}%\")\n   486→\n   487→        # Compute base overhead for bounds\n   488→        base_overhead = r3_art.get(\"step_overhead_us\", 5000)\n   489→        lower, upper = compute_bounds(params, base_overhead)\n   490→\n   491→        lower_list = [lower[n] for n in param_names]\n   492→        upper_list = [upper[n] for n in param_names]\n   493→\n   494→        # Clip x0 to bounds\n   495→        x0_clipped = [max(lo, min(hi, v)) for v, lo, hi in zip(x0, lower_list, upper_list)]\n   496→\n   497→        # CMA-ES configuration\n   498→        sigma0 = 0.1 * np.mean([abs(hi - lo) for lo, hi in zip(lower_list, upper_list)])\n   499→        sigma0 = max(sigma0, 10)\n   500→\n   501→        objective_fn, eval_count = make_objective(\n   502→            r3_art, param_names, exps, alpha, ttft_ms\n   503→        )\n   504→\n   505→        t0 = time.time()\n   506→        opts = cma.CMAOptions()\n   507→        opts[\"maxfevals\"] = max_evals\n   508→        opts[\"timeout\"] = 1800  # 30 min timeout\n   509→        opts[\"bounds\"] = [lower_list, upper_list]\n   510→        opts[\"verbose\"] = -1\n   511→        opts[\"seed\"] = 42\n   512→        opts[\"popsize\"] = 8\n   513→\n   514→        es = cma.CMAEvolutionStrategy(x0_clipped, sigma0, opts)\n   515→        convergence = []\n   516→\n   517→        while not es.stop():\n   518→            solutions = es.ask()\n   519→            fitnesses = [objective_fn(s) for s in solutions]\n   520→            es.tell(solutions, fitnesses)\n   521→            convergence.append(float(es.result.fbest))\n   522→\n   523→        elapsed = time.time() - t0\n   524→        best_x = es.result.xbest\n   525→        best_params = dict(zip(param_names, best_x))\n   526→        best_artifact = param_vector_to_artifact(best_params, r3_art)\n   527→\n   528→        # Evaluate final artifact\n   529→        final_results = evaluate_artifact(best_artifact, exps, ttft_ms)\n   530→        final_e2e = np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in final_results])\n   531→        final_itl = np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in final_results])\n   532→\n   533→        print(f\"\\n  Final:   E2E={final_e2e*100:.1f}% ITL={final_itl*100:.1f}%\")\n   534→        print(f\"  Evals: {eval_count[0]}, Time: {elapsed:.0f}s\")\n   535→\n   536→        # Save artifact\n   537→        art_path = os.path.join(artifacts_dir, f\"{model_group}_optimized.json\")\n   538→        with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   539→            json.dump(best_artifact, f, indent=2)\n   540→\n   541→        for r in final_results:\n   542→            r[\"model_group\"] = model_group\n   543→            r[\"initial_e2e_error\"] = initial_e2e\n   544→            r[\"initial_itl_error\"] = initial_itl\n   545→            r[\"alpha\"] = alpha\n   546→        all_results.extend(final_results)\n   547→\n   548→        optimization_logs[model_group] = {\n   549→            \"n_evals\": eval_count[0],\n   550→            \"elapsed_s\": elapsed,\n   551→            \"initial_mean_e2e\": float(initial_e2e),\n   552→            \"initial_mean_itl\": float(initial_itl),\n   553→            \"best_mean_e2e\": float(final_e2e),\n   554→            \"best_mean_itl\": float(final_itl),\n   555→            \"convergence\": convergence,\n   556→            \"alpha\": alpha,\n   557→        }\n   558→\n   559→    # Compute summary\n   560→    ok_results = [r for r in all_results if r.get(\"status\") == \"ok\"]\n   561→    mean_e2e = np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok_results]) * 100\n   562→    mean_itl = np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok_results]) * 100\n   563→    mean_ttft = np.mean([r[\"ttft_error\"] for r in ok_results]) * 100\n   564→\n   565→    summary = {\n   566→        \"alpha\": alpha,\n   567→        \"n_experiments\": len(ok_results),\n   568→        \"mean_e2e_error_pct\": float(mean_e2e),\n   569→        \"mean_ttft_error_pct\": float(mean_ttft),\n   570→        \"mean_itl_error_pct\": float(mean_itl),\n   571→        \"e2e_under_10pct\": sum(1 for r in ok_results if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.10),\n   572→        \"e2e_under_15pct\": sum(1 for r in ok_results if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.15),\n   573→        \"optimization_logs\": optimization_logs,\n   574→        \"per_experiment\": ok_results,\n   575→    }\n   576→\n   577→    summary_path = os.path.join(output_dir, \"summary.json\")\n   578→    with open(summary_path, \"w\") as f:\n   579→        json.dump(summary, f, indent=2, default=str)\n   580→\n   581→    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n   582→    print(f\"  H1 Results (alpha={alpha}):\")\n   583→    print(f\"  Mean E2E:  {mean_e2e:.1f}%\")\n   584→    print(f\"  Mean TTFT: {mean_ttft:.1f}%\")\n   585→    print(f\"  Mean ITL:  {mean_itl:.1f}%\")\n   586→    print(f\"  E2E < 10%: {summary['e2e_under_10pct']}/{len(ok_results)}\")\n   587→    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n   588→\n   589→    return summary, all_results\n   590→\n   591→\n   592→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   593→# H2: Pareto sweep\n   594→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   595→def run_h2(experiments, output_dir=None):\n   596→    \"\"\"Run H1 with different alpha values to explore Pareto frontier.\"\"\"\n   597→    if output_dir is None:\n   598→        output_dir = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"h2-pareto-sweep\")\n   599→    os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)\n   600→\n   601→    alphas = [0.7, 0.5, 0.3]\n   602→    pareto_points = []\n   603→\n   604→    for alpha in alphas:\n   605→        print(f\"\\n{'#'*60}\")\n   606→        print(f\"  PARETO SWEEP: alpha = {alpha}\")\n   607→        print(f\"{'#'*60}\")\n   608→\n   609→        alpha_dir = os.path.join(output_dir, f\"alpha_{alpha}\")\n   610→        summary, results = run_h1(\n   611→            experiments, alpha=alpha, max_evals=100, output_dir=alpha_dir\n   612→        )\n   613→\n   614→        pareto_points.append({\n   615→            \"alpha\": alpha,\n   616→            \"mean_e2e_pct\": summary[\"mean_e2e_error_pct\"],\n   617→            \"mean_itl_pct\": summary[\"mean_itl_error_pct\"],\n   618→            \"mean_ttft_pct\": summary[\"mean_ttft_error_pct\"],\n   619→            \"e2e_under_10\": summary[\"e2e_under_10pct\"],\n   620→            \"n_experiments\": summary[\"n_experiments\"],\n   621→        })\n   622→\n   623→    # Find knee point (closest to origin in E2E-ITL space)\n   624→    best_idx = 0\n   625→    best_dist = float(\"inf\")\n   626→    for i, pt in enumerate(pareto_points):\n   627→        # Normalize: E2E target 10%, ITL target 15%\n   628→        dist = (pt[\"mean_e2e_pct\"] / 10) ** 2 + (pt[\"mean_itl_pct\"] / 15) ** 2\n   629→        if dist < best_dist:\n   630→            best_dist = dist\n   631→            best_idx = i\n   632→\n   633→    pareto_summary = {\n   634→        \"pareto_points\": pareto_points,\n   635→        \"best_alpha\": pareto_points[best_idx][\"alpha\"],\n   636→        \"best_point\": pareto_points[best_idx],\n   637→        \"knee_distance\": float(best_dist),\n   638→    }\n   639→\n   640→    summary_path = os.path.join(output_dir, \"pareto_summary.json\")\n   641→    with open(summary_path, \"w\") as f:\n   642→        json.dump(pareto_summary, f, indent=2)\n   643→\n   644→    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n   645→    print(f\"  PARETO FRONTIER:\")\n   646→    print(f\"  {'Alpha':>6s} {'E2E%':>8s} {'ITL%':>8s} {'TTFT%':>8s} {'<10%':>5s}\")\n   647→    for pt in pareto_points:\n   648→        marker = \" ← KNEE\" if pt[\"alpha\"] == pareto_points[best_idx][\"alpha\"] else \"\"\n   649→        print(f\"  {pt['alpha']:>6.1f} {pt['mean_e2e_pct']:>7.1f}% \"\n   650→              f\"{pt['mean_itl_pct']:>7.1f}% {pt['mean_ttft_pct']:>7.1f}% \"\n   651→              f\"{pt['e2e_under_10']:>4d}{marker}\")\n   652→    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n   653→\n   654→    return pareto_summary\n   655→\n   656→\n   657→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   658→# H3: LOMO (leave-one-model-out)\n   659→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   660→def run_h3(experiments, best_alpha, output_dir=None):\n   661→    \"\"\"Leave-one-model-out cross-validation with CMA-ES artifacts.\"\"\"\n   662→    if output_dir is None:\n   663→        output_dir = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"h3-lomo\")\n   664→    os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)\n   665→\n   666→    # Get unique model groups\n   667→    model_groups = sorted(set(e[\"model_group\"] for e in experiments))\n   668→    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n   669→    print(f\"  H3: LOMO ({len(model_groups)} folds)\")\n   670→    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n   671→\n   672→    # Load best artifacts (from H2's best alpha)\n   673→    best_artifacts_dir = os.path.join(\n   674→        _SCRIPT_DIR, \"h2-pareto-sweep\", f\"alpha_{best_alpha}\", \"artifacts\"\n   675→    )\n   676→\n   677→    folds = []\n   678→    for holdout_model in model_groups:\n   679→        print(f\"\\n  Fold: holdout={holdout_model}\")\n   680→        holdout_exps = [e for e in experiments if e[\"model_group\"] == holdout_model]\n   681→        # For each donor model, try its artifact on the holdout\n   682→        donor_results = []\n   683→        for donor_model in model_groups:\n   684→            if donor_model == holdout_model:\n   685→                continue\n   686→            art_path = os.path.join(best_artifacts_dir, f\"{donor_model}_optimized.json\")\n   687→            if not os.path.isfile(art_path):\n   688→                continue\n   689→\n   690→            with open(art_path) as f:\n   691→                donor_art = json.load(f)\n   692→\n   693→            ttft_ms = TTFT_CORRECTIONS_MS.get(holdout_model, 0)\n   694→            results = evaluate_artifact(donor_art, holdout_exps, ttft_ms)\n   695→            ok_results = [r for r in results if r.get(\"status\") == \"ok\"]\n   696→            if ok_results:\n   697→                mean_e2e = np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok_results])\n   698→                mean_itl = np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok_results])\n   699→                donor_results.append({\n   700→                    \"donor\": donor_model,\n   701→                    \"mean_e2e_pct\": float(mean_e2e * 100),\n   702→                    \"mean_itl_pct\": float(mean_itl * 100),\n   703→                    \"per_experiment\": ok_results,\n   704→                })\n   705→                print(f\"    Donor {donor_model}: E2E={mean_e2e*100:.1f}% ITL={mean_itl*100:.1f}%\")\n   706→\n   707→        # Best donor for this fold\n   708→        if donor_results:\n   709→            best_donor = min(donor_results, key=lambda x: x[\"mean_e2e_pct\"])\n   710→        else:\n   711→            best_donor = {\"donor\": \"none\", \"mean_e2e_pct\": 999, \"mean_itl_pct\": 999}\n   712→\n   713→        folds.append({\n   714→            \"holdout_model\": holdout_model,\n   715→            \"best_donor\": best_donor[\"donor\"],\n   716→            \"best_donor_e2e_pct\": best_donor[\"mean_e2e_pct\"],\n   717→            \"best_donor_itl_pct\": best_donor.get(\"mean_itl_pct\", 999),\n   718→            \"all_donors\": donor_results,\n   719→        })\n   720→\n   721→    # Summary\n   722→    mean_best_donor_e2e = np.mean([f[\"best_donor_e2e_pct\"] for f in folds])\n   723→    lomo_summary = {\n   724→        \"folds\": folds,\n   725→        \"mean_best_donor_e2e_pct\": float(mean_best_donor_e2e),\n   726→        \"target\": \"<80% MAPE per fold (E2E proxy)\",\n   727→        \"alpha_used\": best_alpha,\n   728→    }\n   729→\n   730→    summary_path = os.path.join(output_dir, \"lomo_summary.json\")\n   731→    with open(summary_path, \"w\") as f:\n   732→        json.dump(lomo_summary, f, indent=2, default=str)\n   733→\n   734→    print(f\"\\n  LOMO Summary:\")\n   735→    print(f\"  {'Holdout':<25s} {'Best Donor':<25s} {'E2E%':>8s} {'ITL%':>8s}\")\n   736→    for fold in folds:\n   737→        print(f\"  {fold['holdout_model']:<25s} {fold['best_donor']:<25s} \"\n   738→              f\"{fold['best_donor_e2e_pct']:>7.1f}% {fold['best_donor_itl_pct']:>7.1f}%\")\n   739→    print(f\"  Mean best-donor E2E: {mean_best_donor_e2e:.1f}%\")\n   740→\n   741→    return lomo_summary\n   742→\n   743→\n   744→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   745→# H4: LOWO (leave-one-workload-out)\n   746→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   747→def run_h4(experiments, best_alpha, output_dir=None):\n   748→    \"\"\"Leave-one-workload-out: check per-model workload variance.\"\"\"\n   749→    if output_dir is None:\n   750→        output_dir = os.path.join(_SCRIPT_DIR, \"h4-lowo\")\n   751→    os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)\n   752→\n   753→    # Load best artifacts\n   754→    best_artifacts_dir = os.path.join(\n   755→        _SCRIPT_DIR, \"h2-pareto-sweep\", f\"alpha_{best_alpha}\", \"artifacts\"\n   756→    )\n   757→\n   758→    # Get unique workloads and models\n   759→    workloads = sorted(set(e[\"workload\"] for e in experiments))\n   760→    model_groups = sorted(set(e[\"model_group\"] for e in experiments))\n   761→\n   762→    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n   763→    print(f\"  H4: LOWO ({len(workloads)} workloads)\")\n   764→    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n   765→\n   766→    # Evaluate each experiment with its model's best artifact\n   767→    per_exp_results = []\n   768→    for exp in experiments:\n   769→        art_path = os.path.join(best_artifacts_dir, f\"{exp['model_group']}_optimized.json\")\n   770→        if not os.path.isfile(art_path):\n   771→            continue\n   772→        with open(art_path) as f:\n   773→            art = json.load(f)\n   774→        ttft_ms = TTFT_CORRECTIONS_MS.get(exp[\"model\"], 0)\n   775→        results = evaluate_artifact(art, [exp], ttft_ms)\n   776→        if results and results[0].get(\"status\") == \"ok\":\n   777→            per_exp_results.append(results[0])\n   778→\n   779→    # Compute per-model workload range\n   780→    model_workload_map = {}\n   781→    for r in per_exp_results:\n   782→        group = MODEL_GROUPS.get(r.get(\"model\", \"\"), r.get(\"model\", \"\"))\n   783→        model_workload_map.setdefault(group, []).append(r)\n   784→\n   785→    model_stats = {}\n   786→    for model, results in sorted(model_workload_map.items()):\n   787→        e2e_errors = [r[\"e2e_error\"] * 100 for r in results]\n   788→        model_stats[model] = {\n   789→            \"workloads\": [r.get(\"workload\", \"?\") for r in results],\n   790→            \"e2e_errors\": e2e_errors,\n   791→            \"e2e_range\": max(e2e_errors) - min(e2e_errors),\n   792→            \"e2e_mean\": np.mean(e2e_errors),\n   793→        }\n   794→\n   795→    # Aggregate E2E across all experiments\n   796→    agg_e2e = np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in per_exp_results])\n   797→    within_2x = sum(\n   798→        1 for r in per_exp_results if r[\"e2e_error\"] <= agg_e2e * 2\n   799→    )\n   800→\n   801→    lowo_summary = {\n   802→        \"per_model_stats\": {m: s for m, s in model_stats.items()},\n   803→        \"aggregate_e2e_pct\": float(agg_e2e * 100),\n   804→        \"within_2x_aggregate\": within_2x,\n   805→        \"total_experiments\": len(per_exp_results),\n   806→        \"alpha_used\": best_alpha,\n   807→    }\n   808→\n   809→    summary_path = os.path.join(output_dir, \"lowo_summary.json\")\n   810→    with open(summary_path, \"w\") as f:\n   811→        json.dump(lowo_summary, f, indent=2, default=str)\n   812→\n   813→    print(f\"\\n  LOWO Summary:\")\n   814→    print(f\"  {'Model':<25s} {'Range (pp)':>10s} {'Mean E2E%':>10s} {'Workloads'}\")\n   815→    for model, stats in sorted(model_stats.items()):\n   816→        wl_str = \", \".join(f\"{w}={e:.1f}%\" for w, e in zip(stats[\"workloads\"], stats[\"e2e_errors\"]))\n   817→        print(f\"  {model:<25s} {stats['e2e_range']:>9.1f}pp {stats['e2e_mean']:>9.1f}% {wl_str}\")\n   818→    print(f\"\\n  Aggregate E2E: {agg_e2e*100:.1f}%\")\n   819→    print(f\"  Within 2x aggregate: {within_2x}/{len(per_exp_results)}\")\n   820→\n   821→    return lowo_summary\n   822→\n   823→\n   824→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   825→# Main\n   826→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   827→def main():\n   828→    print(\"=\" * 60)\n   829→    print(\"  Round 4, Idea 1: Constrained CMA-ES with ITL Penalty\")\n   830→    print(\"=\" * 60)\n   831→\n   832→    # Discover experiments\n   833→    experiments = discover_experiments()\n   834→    print(f\"\\nDiscovered {len(experiments)} experiments\")\n   835→    for exp in experiments:\n   836→        print(f\"  {exp['dirname']}: model={exp['model_group']}, wl={exp['workload']}\")\n   837→\n   838→    if not experiments:\n   839→        print(\"ERROR: No experiments found. Check _DATA_ROOT path.\")\n   840→        sys.exit(1)\n   841→\n   842→    # H1: Run with default alpha=0.5 first to verify infrastructure\n   843→    print(f\"\\n{'#'*60}\")\n   844→    print(\"  H1: Constrained CMA-ES (alpha=0.5)\")\n   845→    print(f\"{'#'*60}\")\n   846→    h1_summary, h1_results = run_h1(experiments, alpha=0.5, max_evals=100)\n   847→\n   848→    # Short-circuit check\n   849→    if h1_summary[\"mean_e2e_error_pct\"] > 25:\n   850→        print(f\"\\nSHORT-CIRCUIT: Mean E2E {h1_summary['mean_e2e_error_pct']:.1f}% > 25%\")\n   851→        print(\"Constrained CMA-ES is significantly worse than R3. Aborting.\")\n   852→        return\n   853→\n   854→    # H2: Pareto sweep\n   855→    print(f\"\\n{'#'*60}\")\n   856→    print(\"  H2: Pareto Sweep\")\n   857→    print(f\"{'#'*60}\")\n   858→    h2_summary = run_h2(experiments)\n   859→    best_alpha = h2_summary[\"best_alpha\"]\n   860→\n   861→    # H3: LOMO\n   862→    print(f\"\\n{'#'*60}\")\n   863→    print(f\"  H3: LOMO (using best alpha={best_alpha})\")\n   864→    print(f\"{'#'*60}\")\n   865→    h3_summary = run_h3(experiments, best_alpha)\n   866→\n   867→    # H4: LOWO\n   868→    print(f\"\\n{'#'*60}\")\n   869→    print(f\"  H4: LOWO (using best alpha={best_alpha})\")\n   870→    print(f\"{'#'*60}\")\n   871→    h4_summary = run_h4(experiments, best_alpha)\n   872→\n   873→    # Final summary\n   874→    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n   875→    print(\"  FINAL SUMMARY\")\n   876→    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n   877→    print(f\"  H1 (alpha=0.5): E2E={h1_summary['mean_e2e_error_pct']:.1f}% \"\n   878→          f\"ITL={h1_summary['mean_itl_error_pct']:.1f}%\")\n   879→    print(f\"  H2 best alpha={best_alpha}: \"\n   880→          f\"E2E={h2_summary['best_point']['mean_e2e_pct']:.1f}% \"\n   881→          f\"ITL={h2_summary['best_point']['mean_itl_pct']:.1f}%\")\n   882→    print(f\"  H3 LOMO mean best-donor E2E: {h3_summary['mean_best_donor_e2e_pct']:.1f}%\")\n   883→    print(f\"  H4 LOWO within 2x: {h4_summary['within_2x_aggregate']}/{h4_summary['total_experiments']}\")\n   884→\n   885→\n   886→if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n   887→    main()\n   888→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017vgie1jSaXiJSc9cebn2B7","session_id":"6c146fd0-2769-4d18-b481-0819d4602c26","uuid":"12d77c83-d8e9-4b91-9ac2-08199b4bfe7a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Gn49AxqCzeSMHbFFDkFHNb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2→\"\"\"Round 3, Idea 3: End-to-End Calibration via Direct E2E Objective.\n     3→\n     4→Runs all three sub-hypotheses:\n     5→  H1: CMA-ES optimization of StepML parameters against BLIS E2E error (trace replay)\n     6→  H2: Same optimization in workload-spec mode\n     7→  H3: Additive correction factors for TTFT/ITL residuals\n     8→\n     9→Uses Round 2's best StepML artifacts as starting point (regime ensemble + overheads).\n    10→CMA-ES treats BLIS as a black-box function: params → E2E error.\n    11→\"\"\"\n    12→\n    13→import copy\n    14→import csv\n    15→import json\n    16→import math\n    17→import os\n    18→import random\n    19→import subprocess\n    20→import sys\n    21→import tempfile\n    22→import time\n    23→\n    24→import cma\n    25→import numpy as np\n    26→import yaml\n    27→\n    28→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    29→# Paths\n    30→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    31→SCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\n    32→REPO_ROOT = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"..\", \"..\", \"..\", \"..\"))\n    33→PACKAGE_ROOT = \"/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package\"\n    34→BLIS_RESEARCH_ROOT = os.path.join(PACKAGE_ROOT, \"BLIS-research\")\n    35→GT_DATA_ROOT = os.path.join(BLIS_RESEARCH_ROOT, \"eval\", \"ground_truth\")\n    36→ORIG_GT_ROOT = os.path.join(PACKAGE_ROOT, \"inference-sim\", \"eval\", \"ground_truth\")\n    37→R2_ARTIFACTS_DIR = os.path.join(\n    38→    BLIS_RESEARCH_ROOT,\n    39→    \"hypotheses\", \"h-stepml\", \"round2\",\n    40→    \"idea-2-regime-ensemble\", \"h3-secondary-method-calibration\",\n    41→    \"output\", \"calibrated_artifacts\",\n    42→)\n    43→BINARY_PATH = os.path.join(REPO_ROOT, \"simulation_worker\")\n    44→BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS = 16\n    45→\n    46→# Model → artifact file mapping\n    47→MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP = {\n    48→    \"llama-2-7b\": \"llama-2-7b_tp1_regime.json\",\n    49→    \"llama-2-70b\": \"llama-2-70b_tp4_regime.json\",\n    50→    \"llama-2-70b-hf\": \"llama-2-70b-hf_tp4_regime.json\",\n    51→    \"codellama-34b\": \"codellama-34b_tp2_regime.json\",\n    52→    \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\": \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1_tp2_regime.json\",\n    53→}\n    54→\n    55→# Models that share the same artifact (grouped for optimization)\n    56→MODEL_GROUPS = {\n    57→    \"llama-2-7b\": [\"llama-2-7b\"],\n    58→    \"llama-2-70b\": [\"llama-2-70b\", \"llama-2-70b-hf\"],\n    59→    \"codellama-34b\": [\"codellama-34b\"],\n    60→    \"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\": [\"mixtral-8x7b-v0-1\"],\n    61→}\n    62→\n    63→\n    64→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    65→# Helpers (reused from Idea 1)\n    66→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    67→def parse_experiment_dir(dirname):\n    68→    import re\n    69→    tp_matches = list(re.finditer(r\"-tp(\\d+)-\", dirname))\n    70→    if not tp_matches:\n    71→        raise ValueError(f\"Cannot parse: {dirname}\")\n    72→    last_tp = tp_matches[-1]\n    73→    if re.match(r\"^\\d{8}-\\d{6}-\", dirname):\n    74→        model = dirname[16:last_tp.start()]\n    75→    elif re.match(r\"^\\d{8}-\", dirname):\n    76→        model = dirname[9:last_tp.start()]\n    77→    else:\n    78→        model = dirname[:last_tp.start()]\n    79→    return {\n    80→        \"model\": model,\n    81→        \"tp\": int(last_tp.group(1)),\n    82→        \"workload\": dirname[last_tp.end():],\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→\n    86→def load_ground_truth(experiment_dir):\n    87→    summary_path = os.path.join(\n    88→        experiment_dir, \"results\", \"summary_lifecycle_metrics.json\"\n    89→    )\n    90→    with open(summary_path) as f:\n    91→        data = json.load(f)\n    92→    successes = data.get(\"successes\", {})\n    93→    latency = successes.get(\"latency\", {})\n    94→    return {\n    95→        \"e2e_mean_s\": latency.get(\"request_latency\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n    96→        \"ttft_mean_s\": latency.get(\"time_to_first_token\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n    97→        \"itl_mean_s\": latency.get(\"inter_token_latency\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n    98→        \"num_requests\": data.get(\"load_summary\", {}).get(\"count\", 0),\n    99→        \"prompt_len_mean\": successes.get(\"prompt_len\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n   100→        \"output_len_mean\": successes.get(\"output_len\", {}).get(\"mean\", 0),\n   101→        \"throughput_rps\": successes.get(\"throughput\", {}).get(\"requests_per_sec\", 0),\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→\n   105→def load_exp_config(experiment_dir):\n   106→    with open(os.path.join(experiment_dir, \"exp-config.yaml\")) as f:\n   107→        return yaml.safe_load(f)\n   108→\n   109→\n   110→def extract_kv_blocks(experiment_dir):\n   111→    import re\n   112→    vllm_log = os.path.join(experiment_dir, \"vllm.log\")\n   113→    if not os.path.isfile(vllm_log):\n   114→        return None\n   115→    pattern = re.compile(r\"GPU KV cache size:\\s+([\\d,]+)\\s+tokens\")\n   116→    with open(vllm_log) as f:\n   117→        for line in f:\n   118→            m = pattern.search(line)\n   119→            if m:\n   120→                return int(m.group(1).replace(\",\", \"\")) // BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS\n   121→    return None\n   122→\n   123→\n   124→def extract_cpu_kv_blocks(experiment_dir):\n   125→    import re\n   126→    vllm_log = os.path.join(experiment_dir, \"vllm.log\")\n   127→    if not os.path.isfile(vllm_log):\n   128→        return 0\n   129→    cpu_bytes = None\n   130→    kv_shape = None\n   131→    with open(vllm_log) as f:\n   132→        for line in f:\n   133→            m = re.search(r\"cpu_bytes_to_use['\\\"]?:\\s*([\\d.]+)\", line)\n   134→            if m and cpu_bytes is None:\n   135→                cpu_bytes = float(m.group(1))\n   136→            m = re.search(\n   137→                r\"cross layer KV cache of shape \\((\\d+),\\s*(\\d+),\\s*(\\d+),\\s*(\\d+),\\s*(\\d+),\\s*(\\d+)\\)\",\n   138→                line,\n   139→            )\n   140→            if m and kv_shape is None:\n   141→                kv_shape = tuple(int(m.group(i)) for i in range(1, 7))\n   142→    if cpu_bytes is None or kv_shape is None or cpu_bytes == 0:\n   143→        return 0\n   144→    _, num_layers, _, block_size, num_kv_heads, head_dim = kv_shape\n   145→    per_block_bytes = num_layers * 2 * block_size * num_kv_heads * head_dim * 2\n   146→    return int(cpu_bytes) // per_block_bytes\n   147→\n   148→\n   149→def convert_lifecycle_to_csv(lifecycle_path, output_csv, model_name, seed=42):\n   150→    with open(lifecycle_path) as f:\n   151→        data = json.load(f)\n   152→    if not data:\n   153→        raise ValueError(f\"Empty lifecycle data: {lifecycle_path}\")\n   154→    rng = random.Random(seed)\n   155→    base_time = min(entry[\"start_time\"] for entry in data)\n   156→    rows = []\n   157→    for i, entry in enumerate(data):\n   158→        info = entry.get(\"info\", {})\n   159→        input_count = info.get(\"input_tokens\", 0)\n   160→        output_count = info.get(\"output_tokens\", 0)\n   161→        arrival_s = entry[\"start_time\"] - base_time\n   162→        input_tokens = [rng.randint(0, 31999) for _ in range(input_count)]\n   163→        output_tokens = [rng.randint(0, 31999) for _ in range(output_count)]\n   164→        rows.append((arrival_s, i, model_name, input_tokens, output_tokens))\n   165→    rows.sort(key=lambda x: x[0])\n   166→    with open(output_csv, \"w\") as f:\n   167→        f.write(\"arrival_time,request_id,model,prefill_tokens,decode_tokens\\n\")\n   168→        for arrival_s, req_id, model, inp, out in rows:\n   169→            f.write(\n   170→                f\"{arrival_s:.6f},request_{req_id},{model},\"\n   171→                f'\"{json.dumps(inp)}\",\"{json.dumps(out)}\"\\n'\n   172→            )\n   173→    return {\n   174→        \"num_requests\": len(rows),\n   175→        \"duration_s\": (rows[-1][0] - rows[0][0]) if len(rows) > 1 else 0,\n   176→    }\n   177→\n   178→\n   179→def compute_error(predicted, observed):\n   180→    if observed == 0:\n   181→        return float(\"inf\") if predicted != 0 else 0.0\n   182→    return abs(predicted - observed) / observed\n   183→\n   184→\n   185→def parse_blis_stdout(stdout):\n   186→    lines = stdout.split(\"\\n\")\n   187→    json_lines = []\n   188→    in_json = False\n   189→    brace_depth = 0\n   190→    for line in lines:\n   191→        if \"Simulation Metrics\" in line:\n   192→            in_json = False\n   193→            json_lines = []\n   194→            continue\n   195→        if not in_json and line.strip().startswith(\"{\"):\n   196→            in_json = True\n   197→        if in_json:\n   198→            json_lines.append(line)\n   199→            brace_depth += line.count(\"{\") - line.count(\"}\")\n   200→            if brace_depth <= 0:\n   201→                break\n   202→    if not json_lines:\n   203→        return None\n   204→    try:\n   205→        metrics = json.loads(\"\\n\".join(json_lines))\n   206→    except json.JSONDecodeError:\n   207→        return None\n   208→    return {\n   209→        \"e2e_mean_ms\": metrics.get(\"e2e_mean_ms\", 0),\n   210→        \"ttft_mean_ms\": metrics.get(\"ttft_mean_ms\", 0),\n   211→        \"itl_mean_ms\": metrics.get(\"itl_mean_ms\", 0),\n   212→        \"completed_requests\": metrics.get(\"completed_requests\", 0),\n   213→    }\n   214→\n   215→\n   216→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   217→# Artifact manipulation\n   218→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   219→def load_artifact(model_name):\n   220→    \"\"\"Load the Round 2 best artifact for a given model.\"\"\"\n   221→    artifact_file = MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP.get(model_name)\n   222→    if artifact_file is None:\n   223→        raise ValueError(f\"No artifact for model: {model_name}\")\n   224→    path = os.path.join(R2_ARTIFACTS_DIR, artifact_file)\n   225→    with open(path) as f:\n   226→        return json.load(f)\n   227→\n   228→\n   229→def artifact_to_param_vector(artifact):\n   230→    \"\"\"Extract optimizable parameters from a StepML artifact.\n   231→\n   232→    Parameter vector layout:\n   233→      [step_overhead_us, step_overhead_per_req_us,\n   234→       scheduling_processing_time_us, preemption_processing_time_us,\n   235→       output_token_processing_time_us,\n   236→       queueing_intercept,\n   237→       decode_only_intercept, decode_only_decode_tokens, decode_only_num_decode_reqs,\n   238→       mixed_intercept, mixed_prefill_tokens, mixed_decode_tokens,\n   239→       mixed_num_prefill_reqs, mixed_num_decode_reqs]\n   240→\n   241→    Returns (param_vector, param_names) tuple.\n   242→    \"\"\"\n   243→    params = []\n   244→    names = []\n   245→\n   246→    # Global overhead parameters\n   247→    params.append(artifact.get(\"step_overhead_us\", 0))\n   248→    names.append(\"step_overhead_us\")\n   249→\n   250→    params.append(artifact.get(\"step_overhead_per_req_us\", 0))\n   251→    names.append(\"step_overhead_per_req_us\")\n   252→\n   253→    params.append(artifact.get(\"scheduling_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   254→    names.append(\"scheduling_processing_time_us\")\n   255→\n   256→    params.append(artifact.get(\"preemption_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   257→    names.append(\"preemption_processing_time_us\")\n   258→\n   259→    params.append(artifact.get(\"output_token_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   260→    names.append(\"output_token_processing_time_us\")\n   261→\n   262→    # Queueing time intercept\n   263→    qt = artifact.get(\"queueing_time\")\n   264→    if qt:\n   265→        params.append(qt.get(\"intercept\", 0))\n   266→    else:\n   267→        params.append(0)\n   268→    names.append(\"queueing_intercept\")\n   269→\n   270→    # Step time regime parameters\n   271→    regimes = artifact.get(\"step_time_regimes\", [])\n   272→    for regime in regimes:\n   273→        prefix = regime[\"name\"]\n   274→        model_data = regime[\"model\"]\n   275→        params.append(model_data.get(\"intercept\", 0))\n   276→        names.append(f\"{prefix}_intercept\")\n   277→\n   278→        # Extract feature coefficients in sorted order for reproducibility\n   279→        coeffs = model_data.get(\"feature_coefficients\", {})\n   280→        for feat in sorted(coeffs.keys()):\n   281→            params.append(coeffs[feat])\n   282→            names.append(f\"{prefix}_{feat}\")\n   283→\n   284→    return np.array(params, dtype=np.float64), names\n   285→\n   286→\n   287→def param_vector_to_artifact(params, names, base_artifact):\n   288→    \"\"\"Reconstruct a StepML artifact from an optimized parameter vector.\"\"\"\n   289→    artifact = copy.deepcopy(base_artifact)\n   290→    param_dict = dict(zip(names, params))\n   291→\n   292→    artifact[\"step_overhead_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"step_overhead_us\", 0))\n   293→    artifact[\"step_overhead_per_req_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"step_overhead_per_req_us\", 0))\n   294→    artifact[\"scheduling_processing_time_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"scheduling_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   295→    artifact[\"preemption_processing_time_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"preemption_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   296→    artifact[\"output_token_processing_time_us\"] = max(0, param_dict.get(\"output_token_processing_time_us\", 0))\n   297→\n   298→    # Queueing time\n   299→    qt_intercept = param_dict.get(\"queueing_intercept\", 0)\n   300→    if artifact.get(\"queueing_time\"):\n   301→        artifact[\"queueing_time\"][\"intercept\"] = qt_intercept\n   302→    else:\n   303→        artifact[\"queueing_time\"] = {\n   304→            \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   305→            \"intercept\": qt_intercept,\n   306→            \"feature_coefficients\": {},\n   307→        }\n   308→\n   309→    # Regime coefficients\n   310→    for regime in artifact.get(\"step_time_regimes\", []):\n   311→        prefix = regime[\"name\"]\n   312→        intercept_key = f\"{prefix}_intercept\"\n   313→        if intercept_key in param_dict:\n   314→            regime[\"model\"][\"intercept\"] = param_dict[intercept_key]\n   315→\n   316→        coeffs = regime[\"model\"].get(\"feature_coefficients\", {})\n   317→        for feat in list(coeffs.keys()):\n   318→            key = f\"{prefix}_{feat}\"\n   319→            if key in param_dict:\n   320→                coeffs[feat] = param_dict[key]\n   321→\n   322→    return artifact\n   323→\n   324→\n   325→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   326→# BLIS execution\n   327→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   328→def run_blis_trace(trace_csv, exp_config, kv_blocks, artifact_path, horizon_us,\n   329→                   cpu_kv_blocks=0):\n   330→    \"\"\"Run BLIS in trace replay mode with a StepML artifact.\"\"\"\n   331→    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix=\".json\", delete=False) as f:\n   332→        results_path = f.name\n   333→    cmd = [\n   334→        BINARY_PATH, \"run\",\n   335→        \"--model\", exp_config.get(\"model\", \"unknown\"),\n   336→        \"--workload\", \"traces\",\n   337→        \"--workload-traces-filepath\", trace_csv,\n   338→        \"--tp\", str(exp_config.get(\"tensor_parallelism\", 1)),\n   339→        \"--max-model-len\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_model_len\", 4096)),\n   340→        \"--max-num-running-reqs\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_seqs\", 128)),\n   341→        \"--max-num-scheduled-tokens\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_batched_tokens\", 2048)),\n   342→        \"--total-kv-blocks\", str(kv_blocks),\n   343→        \"--block-size-in-tokens\", str(BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS),\n   344→        \"--horizon\", str(horizon_us),\n   345→        \"--alpha-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   346→        \"--beta-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   347→        \"--stepml-model\", artifact_path,\n   348→        \"--results-path\", results_path,\n   349→        \"--log\", \"error\",\n   350→    ]\n   351→    if cpu_kv_blocks > 0:\n   352→        cmd.extend([\"--kv-cpu-blocks\", str(cpu_kv_blocks)])\n   353→\n   354→    try:\n   355→        result = subprocess.run(\n   356→            cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=300,\n   357→            cwd=os.path.dirname(BINARY_PATH),\n   358→        )\n   359→    except (subprocess.TimeoutExpired, FileNotFoundError):\n   360→        return None\n   361→    finally:\n   362→        if os.path.exists(results_path):\n   363→            os.unlink(results_path)\n   364→\n   365→    if result.returncode != 0:\n   366→        return None\n   367→    return parse_blis_stdout(result.stdout)\n   368→\n   369→\n   370→def run_blis_workload_spec(spec_path, exp_config, kv_blocks, artifact_path,\n   371→                           cpu_kv_blocks=0):\n   372→    \"\"\"Run BLIS in workload-spec mode with a StepML artifact.\"\"\"\n   373→    with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(suffix=\".json\", delete=False) as f:\n   374→        results_path = f.name\n   375→    cmd = [\n   376→        BINARY_PATH, \"run\",\n   377→        \"--model\", exp_config.get(\"model\", \"unknown\"),\n   378→        \"--workload-spec\", spec_path,\n   379→        \"--tp\", str(exp_config.get(\"tensor_parallelism\", 1)),\n   380→        \"--max-model-len\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_model_len\", 4096)),\n   381→        \"--max-num-running-reqs\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_seqs\", 128)),\n   382→        \"--max-num-scheduled-tokens\", str(exp_config.get(\"max_num_batched_tokens\", 2048)),\n   383→        \"--total-kv-blocks\", str(kv_blocks),\n   384→        \"--block-size-in-tokens\", str(BLOCK_SIZE_TOKENS),\n   385→        \"--alpha-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   386→        \"--beta-coeffs=1,0,0\",\n   387→        \"--stepml-model\", artifact_path,\n   388→        \"--results-path\", results_path,\n   389→        \"--log\", \"error\",\n   390→    ]\n   391→    if cpu_kv_blocks > 0:\n   392→        cmd.extend([\"--kv-cpu-blocks\", str(cpu_kv_blocks)])\n   393→\n   394→    try:\n   395→        result = subprocess.run(\n   396→            cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=300,\n   397→            cwd=os.path.dirname(BINARY_PATH),\n   398→        )\n   399→    except (subprocess.TimeoutExpired, FileNotFoundError):\n   400→        return None\n   401→    finally:\n   402→        if os.path.exists(results_path):\n   403→            os.unlink(results_path)\n   404→\n   405→    if result.returncode != 0:\n   406→        return None\n   407→    return parse_blis_stdout(result.stdout)\n   408→\n   409→\n   410→def build_workload_spec(profile, ground_truth):\n   411→    \"\"\"Build a workload-spec from inference-perf profile.\"\"\"\n   412→    data = profile.get(\"data\", {})\n   413→    load_config = profile.get(\"load\", {})\n   414→    sp = data.get(\"shared_prefix\", {})\n   415→\n   416→    stages = []\n   417→    for stage in load_config.get(\"stages\", []):\n   418→        stages.append({\"rate\": stage[\"rate\"], \"duration\": stage[\"duration\"]})\n   419→    if not stages:\n   420→        num_requests = ground_truth.get(\"num_requests\", 1000)\n   421→        rps = ground_truth.get(\"throughput_rps\", 10)\n   422→        duration = int(num_requests / rps) + 60\n   423→        stages.append({\"rate\": rps, \"duration\": duration})\n   424→\n   425→    total_duration_s = sum(s[\"duration\"] for s in stages)\n   426→    total_requests = sum(s[\"rate\"] * s[\"duration\"] for s in stages)\n   427→    horizon_us = int(total_duration_s * 1_000_000) + 60_000_000\n   428→    aggregate_rate = sum(s[\"rate\"] * s[\"duration\"] for s in stages) / total_duration_s\n   429→\n   430→    return {\n   431→        \"version\": \"2\",\n   432→        \"seed\": 42,\n   433→        \"num_requests\": int(total_requests),\n   434→        \"horizon\": horizon_us,\n   435→        \"aggregate_rate\": aggregate_rate,\n   436→        \"inference_perf\": {\n   437→            \"stages\": stages,\n   438→            \"shared_prefix\": {\n   439→                \"num_unique_system_prompts\": sp.get(\"num_unique_system_prompts\", 9),\n   440→                \"num_users_per_system_prompt\": sp.get(\"num_users_per_system_prompt\", 5),\n   441→                \"system_prompt_len\": sp.get(\"system_prompt_len\", 100),\n   442→                \"question_len\": sp.get(\"question_len\", int(ground_truth.get(\"prompt_len_mean\", 500))),\n   443→                \"output_len\": sp.get(\"output_len\", int(ground_truth.get(\"output_len_mean\", 250))),\n   444→                \"enable_multi_turn_chat\": sp.get(\"enable_multi_turn_chat\", False),\n   445→            },\n   446→        },\n   447→    }\n   448→\n   449→\n   450→def load_profile(experiment_dir):\n   451→    profile_path = os.path.join(experiment_dir, \"profile.yaml\")\n   452→    if not os.path.isfile(profile_path):\n   453→        return None\n   454→    with open(profile_path) as f:\n   455→        content = f.read()\n   456→    try:\n   457→        return json.loads(content)\n   458→    except json.JSONDecodeError:\n   459→        return yaml.safe_load(content)\n   460→\n   461→\n   462→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   463→# Experiment discovery\n   464→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   465→def discover_experiments():\n   466→    \"\"\"Find all experiments with lifecycle data.\"\"\"\n   467→    experiments = []\n   468→    for dirname in sorted(os.listdir(GT_DATA_ROOT)):\n   469→        dirpath = os.path.join(GT_DATA_ROOT, dirname)\n   470→        if not os.path.isdir(dirpath):\n   471→            continue\n   472→        lifecycle_path = os.path.join(dirpath, \"results\", \"per_request_lifecycle_metrics.json\")\n   473→        if not os.path.isfile(lifecycle_path):\n   474→            continue\n   475→        try:\n   476→            meta = parse_experiment_dir(dirname)\n   477→        except ValueError:\n   478→            continue\n   479→\n   480→        kv_blocks = extract_kv_blocks(dirpath)\n   481→        if kv_blocks is None:\n   482→            continue\n   483→        cpu_kv_blocks = extract_cpu_kv_blocks(dirpath)\n   484→        exp_config = load_exp_config(dirpath)\n   485→        gt = load_ground_truth(dirpath)\n   486→\n   487→        experiments.append({\n   488→            \"dirname\": dirname,\n   489→            \"dirpath\": dirpath,\n   490→            \"meta\": meta,\n   491→            \"lifecycle_path\": lifecycle_path,\n   492→            \"kv_blocks\": kv_blocks,\n   493→            \"cpu_kv_blocks\": cpu_kv_blocks,\n   494→            \"exp_config\": exp_config,\n   495→            \"gt\": gt,\n   496→        })\n   497→    return experiments\n   498→\n   499→\n   500→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   501→# H1: CMA-ES E2E optimization with trace replay\n   502→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   503→def run_h1(experiments, tmpdir):\n   504→    \"\"\"H1: CMA-ES optimization of StepML parameters against BLIS E2E error.\"\"\"\n   505→    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n   506→    print(\"H1: CMA-ES E2E Optimization with Trace Replay\")\n   507→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   508→\n   509→    # Group experiments by model for per-model optimization\n   510→    model_experiments = {}\n   511→    for exp in experiments:\n   512→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   513→        # Map to canonical model name for artifact lookup\n   514→        canonical = model\n   515→        for group_key, variants in MODEL_GROUPS.items():\n   516→            if model in variants:\n   517→                canonical = group_key\n   518→                break\n   519→        if canonical not in model_experiments:\n   520→            model_experiments[canonical] = []\n   521→        model_experiments[canonical].append(exp)\n   522→\n   523→    # Prepare trace CSV files for all experiments\n   524→    trace_csvs = {}\n   525→    for exp in experiments:\n   526→        csv_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"{exp['dirname']}_trace.csv\")\n   527→        trace_stats = convert_lifecycle_to_csv(\n   528→            exp[\"lifecycle_path\"], csv_path,\n   529→            model_name=exp[\"exp_config\"].get(\"model\", exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]),\n   530→        )\n   531→        horizon_us = int((trace_stats[\"duration_s\"] + 120) * 1_000_000)\n   532→        trace_csvs[exp[\"dirname\"]] = (csv_path, horizon_us)\n   533→\n   534→    # Run initial baseline (Round 2 coefficients)\n   535→    print(\"\\n--- Initial Baseline (Round 2 coefficients) ---\")\n   536→    initial_results = {}\n   537→    for exp in experiments:\n   538→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   539→        artifact = load_artifact(model)\n   540→        art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"{exp['dirname']}_initial.json\")\n   541→        with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   542→            json.dump(artifact, f)\n   543→        csv_path, horizon_us = trace_csvs[exp[\"dirname\"]]\n   544→        blis = run_blis_trace(\n   545→            csv_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   546→            horizon_us, exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   547→        )\n   548→        if blis:\n   549→            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   550→            initial_results[exp[\"dirname\"]] = {\n   551→                \"blis\": blis, \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n   552→                \"ttft_error\": compute_error(blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000),\n   553→                \"itl_error\": compute_error(blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000),\n   554→            }\n   555→            print(f\"  {exp['dirname']}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   556→        else:\n   557→            print(f\"  {exp['dirname']}: BLIS FAILED\")\n   558→\n   559→    # Per-model CMA-ES optimization\n   560→    optimized_artifacts = {}\n   561→    optimization_logs = {}\n   562→\n   563→    for canonical_model, exps in model_experiments.items():\n   564→        print(f\"\\n--- Optimizing: {canonical_model} ({len(exps)} experiments) ---\")\n   565→\n   566→        # Load base artifact\n   567→        base_artifact = load_artifact(canonical_model)\n   568→        initial_params, param_names = artifact_to_param_vector(base_artifact)\n   569→        n_params = len(initial_params)\n   570→        print(f\"  Parameters: {n_params} ({', '.join(param_names[:5])}...)\")\n   571→        print(f\"  Initial: {dict(zip(param_names[:3], initial_params[:3]))}\")\n   572→\n   573→        # Define bounds: each param can vary between 0.1x and 10x initial\n   574→        # For zero initial values, use a reasonable range\n   575→        lower_bounds = []\n   576→        upper_bounds = []\n   577→        for i, (p, name) in enumerate(zip(initial_params, param_names)):\n   578→            if \"overhead\" in name and \"per_req\" not in name:\n   579→                # Step overhead: must stay positive, allow wide range\n   580→                lower_bounds.append(max(500, p * 0.3))\n   581→                upper_bounds.append(p * 5.0)\n   582→            elif \"processing_time\" in name:\n   583→                lower_bounds.append(0)\n   584→                upper_bounds.append(max(5000, abs(p) * 20))\n   585→            elif \"intercept\" in name:\n   586→                lower_bounds.append(p - abs(p) * 5 - 5000)\n   587→                upper_bounds.append(p + abs(p) * 5 + 5000)\n   588→            else:\n   589→                # Coefficients: allow sign flips\n   590→                lower_bounds.append(p - abs(p) * 5 - 100)\n   591→                upper_bounds.append(p + abs(p) * 5 + 100)\n   592→\n   593→        # CMA-ES sigma: 30% of initial magnitude or 100 for near-zero params\n   594→        sigma0 = max(100, 0.3 * np.mean(np.abs(initial_params[initial_params != 0])))\n   595→\n   596→        eval_count = 0\n   597→        convergence_log = []\n   598→\n   599→        def objective(params):\n   600→            \"\"\"Evaluate mean E2E error across experiments for this model.\"\"\"\n   601→            nonlocal eval_count\n   602→            eval_count += 1\n   603→\n   604→            # Reconstruct artifact\n   605→            artifact = param_vector_to_artifact(params, param_names, base_artifact)\n   606→            art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"cma_{canonical_model}_{eval_count}.json\")\n   607→            with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   608→                json.dump(artifact, f)\n   609→\n   610→            errors = []\n   611→            for exp in exps:\n   612→                csv_path, horizon_us = trace_csvs[exp[\"dirname\"]]\n   613→                blis = run_blis_trace(\n   614→                    csv_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   615→                    horizon_us, exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   616→                )\n   617→                if blis is None:\n   618→                    errors.append(5.0)  # Penalty for failed runs\n   619→                else:\n   620→                    e2e_err = compute_error(\n   621→                        blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000\n   622→                    )\n   623→                    errors.append(e2e_err)\n   624→\n   625→            os.unlink(art_path)\n   626→            mean_err = np.mean(errors)\n   627→            convergence_log.append({\"eval\": eval_count, \"mean_e2e_error\": float(mean_err)})\n   628→\n   629→            if eval_count % 10 == 0:\n   630→                print(f\"    Eval {eval_count}: mean E2E error = {mean_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   631→\n   632→            return mean_err\n   633→\n   634→        # Run CMA-ES\n   635→        opts = cma.CMAOptions()\n   636→        opts[\"maxfevals\"] = 150  # Budget: 150 evaluations per model\n   637→        opts[\"timeout\"] = 1800  # 30 min timeout per model\n   638→        opts[\"bounds\"] = [lower_bounds, upper_bounds]\n   639→        opts[\"verbose\"] = -1  # Suppress CMA output\n   640→        opts[\"seed\"] = 42\n   641→        opts[\"popsize\"] = 8  # Small population for fast iteration\n   642→\n   643→        t0 = time.time()\n   644→        es = cma.CMAEvolutionStrategy(initial_params.tolist(), sigma0, opts)\n   645→        es.optimize(objective)\n   646→        elapsed = time.time() - t0\n   647→\n   648→        best_params = es.result.xbest\n   649→        best_error = es.result.fbest\n   650→        print(f\"  CMA-ES done in {elapsed:.0f}s, {eval_count} evals\")\n   651→        print(f\"  Best mean E2E error: {best_error*100:.1f}%\")\n   652→\n   653→        # Build optimized artifact\n   654→        optimized_art = param_vector_to_artifact(best_params, param_names, base_artifact)\n   655→        optimized_artifacts[canonical_model] = optimized_art\n   656→\n   657→        # Log parameter changes\n   658→        param_changes = {}\n   659→        for name, old, new in zip(param_names, initial_params, best_params):\n   660→            pct_change = ((new - old) / abs(old) * 100) if old != 0 else (new * 100 if new != 0 else 0)\n   661→            param_changes[name] = {\n   662→                \"initial\": float(old), \"optimized\": float(new),\n   663→                \"pct_change\": float(pct_change),\n   664→            }\n   665→\n   666→        optimization_logs[canonical_model] = {\n   667→            \"n_evals\": eval_count,\n   668→            \"elapsed_s\": elapsed,\n   669→            \"initial_mean_e2e\": float(np.mean([\n   670→                initial_results.get(e[\"dirname\"], {}).get(\"e2e_error\", 1.0)\n   671→                for e in exps\n   672→            ])),\n   673→            \"best_mean_e2e\": float(best_error),\n   674→            \"param_changes\": param_changes,\n   675→            \"convergence\": convergence_log,\n   676→        }\n   677→\n   678→    # Final evaluation with optimized artifacts\n   679→    print(\"\\n--- Final Evaluation (Optimized) ---\")\n   680→    h1_results = []\n   681→    for exp in experiments:\n   682→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   683→        # Find canonical model\n   684→        canonical = model\n   685→        for group_key, variants in MODEL_GROUPS.items():\n   686→            if model in variants:\n   687→                canonical = group_key\n   688→                break\n   689→\n   690→        optimized_art = optimized_artifacts.get(canonical)\n   691→        if optimized_art is None:\n   692→            print(f\"  {exp['dirname']}: NO OPTIMIZED ARTIFACT\")\n   693→            continue\n   694→\n   695→        # For grouped models (llama-2-70b variants), need to use the right base artifact\n   696→        if model != canonical and model in MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP:\n   697→            # Load the variant's base artifact and apply the same parameter changes\n   698→            variant_base = load_artifact(model)\n   699→            variant_params, variant_names = artifact_to_param_vector(variant_base)\n   700→            # Apply the same relative changes from canonical optimization\n   701→            canon_base = load_artifact(canonical)\n   702→            canon_initial, canon_names = artifact_to_param_vector(canon_base)\n   703→            canon_optimized, _ = artifact_to_param_vector(optimized_art)\n   704→\n   705→            # Apply proportional changes\n   706→            new_params = np.copy(variant_params)\n   707→            for i, name in enumerate(variant_names):\n   708→                if i < len(canon_names) and name == canon_names[i]:\n   709→                    if canon_initial[i] != 0:\n   710→                        ratio = canon_optimized[i] / canon_initial[i]\n   711→                        new_params[i] = variant_params[i] * ratio\n   712→                    else:\n   713→                        new_params[i] = canon_optimized[i]\n   714→            art_to_use = param_vector_to_artifact(new_params, variant_names, variant_base)\n   715→        else:\n   716→            art_to_use = optimized_art\n   717→\n   718→        art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"final_{exp['dirname']}.json\")\n   719→        with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   720→            json.dump(art_to_use, f)\n   721→\n   722→        csv_path, horizon_us = trace_csvs[exp[\"dirname\"]]\n   723→        blis = run_blis_trace(\n   724→            csv_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   725→            horizon_us, exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   726→        )\n   727→\n   728→        if blis:\n   729→            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   730→            ttft_err = compute_error(blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   731→            itl_err = compute_error(blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   732→\n   733→            # Get initial for comparison\n   734→            init = initial_results.get(exp[\"dirname\"], {})\n   735→            init_e2e = init.get(\"e2e_error\", 1.0) * 100\n   736→\n   737→            print(f\"  {exp['dirname']}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}% (was {init_e2e:.1f}%), \"\n   738→                  f\"TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   739→\n   740→            h1_results.append({\n   741→                \"experiment\": exp[\"dirname\"],\n   742→                \"model\": model,\n   743→                \"workload\": exp[\"meta\"][\"workload\"],\n   744→                \"tp\": exp[\"meta\"][\"tp\"],\n   745→                \"gt_e2e_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   746→                \"gt_ttft_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   747→                \"gt_itl_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   748→                \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n   749→                \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n   750→                \"blis_itl_ms\": blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n   751→                \"blis_completed\": blis[\"completed_requests\"],\n   752→                \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n   753→                \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n   754→                \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n   755→                \"initial_e2e_error\": init.get(\"e2e_error\", None),\n   756→            })\n   757→\n   758→        # Save the optimized artifact for this experiment\n   759→        final_art_dir = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"h1-trace-e2e-opt\", \"artifacts\")\n   760→        os.makedirs(final_art_dir, exist_ok=True)\n   761→        final_art_path = os.path.join(final_art_dir, f\"{model}_optimized.json\")\n   762→        with open(final_art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   763→            json.dump(art_to_use, f, indent=2)\n   764→\n   765→    return h1_results, initial_results, optimization_logs, optimized_artifacts\n   766→\n   767→\n   768→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   769→# H2: Workload-spec mode E2E optimization\n   770→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   771→def run_h2(experiments, optimized_artifacts, tmpdir):\n   772→    \"\"\"H2: Run optimized artifacts in workload-spec mode.\"\"\"\n   773→    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n   774→    print(\"H2: Workload-Spec Mode with E2E-Optimized Coefficients\")\n   775→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   776→\n   777→    h2_results = []\n   778→\n   779→    for exp in experiments:\n   780→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   781→        dirname = exp[\"dirname\"]\n   782→\n   783→        # Find canonical model\n   784→        canonical = model\n   785→        for group_key, variants in MODEL_GROUPS.items():\n   786→            if model in variants:\n   787→                canonical = group_key\n   788→                break\n   789→\n   790→        # Try to load profile from original eval directory\n   791→        orig_dir = os.path.join(ORIG_GT_ROOT, dirname)\n   792→        profile = load_profile(orig_dir) if os.path.isdir(orig_dir) else None\n   793→        if profile is None:\n   794→            profile = load_profile(exp[\"dirpath\"])\n   795→        if profile is None:\n   796→            print(f\"  {dirname}: SKIP (no profile)\")\n   797→            continue\n   798→\n   799→        # Build workload spec\n   800→        spec = build_workload_spec(profile, exp[\"gt\"])\n   801→        spec_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"{dirname}_spec.yaml\")\n   802→        with open(spec_path, \"w\") as f:\n   803→            yaml.dump(spec, f, default_flow_style=False)\n   804→\n   805→        # Use the same optimized artifact from H1\n   806→        optimized_art = optimized_artifacts.get(canonical)\n   807→        if optimized_art is None:\n   808→            print(f\"  {dirname}: NO OPTIMIZED ARTIFACT\")\n   809→            continue\n   810→\n   811→        # Handle variant models\n   812→        if model != canonical and model in MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP:\n   813→            variant_base = load_artifact(model)\n   814→            variant_params, variant_names = artifact_to_param_vector(variant_base)\n   815→            canon_base = load_artifact(canonical)\n   816→            canon_initial, canon_names = artifact_to_param_vector(canon_base)\n   817→            canon_optimized, _ = artifact_to_param_vector(optimized_art)\n   818→            new_params = np.copy(variant_params)\n   819→            for i, name in enumerate(variant_names):\n   820→                if i < len(canon_names) and name == canon_names[i]:\n   821→                    if canon_initial[i] != 0:\n   822→                        new_params[i] = variant_params[i] * (canon_optimized[i] / canon_initial[i])\n   823→                    else:\n   824→                        new_params[i] = canon_optimized[i]\n   825→            art_to_use = param_vector_to_artifact(new_params, variant_names, variant_base)\n   826→        else:\n   827→            art_to_use = optimized_art\n   828→\n   829→        art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"h2_{dirname}.json\")\n   830→        with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   831→            json.dump(art_to_use, f)\n   832→\n   833→        blis = run_blis_workload_spec(\n   834→            spec_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   835→            exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   836→        )\n   837→\n   838→        if blis:\n   839→            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   840→            ttft_err = compute_error(blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   841→            itl_err = compute_error(blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n   842→            print(f\"  {dirname}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%, TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n   843→\n   844→            h2_results.append({\n   845→                \"experiment\": dirname,\n   846→                \"model\": model,\n   847→                \"workload\": exp[\"meta\"][\"workload\"],\n   848→                \"tp\": exp[\"meta\"][\"tp\"],\n   849→                \"gt_e2e_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   850→                \"gt_ttft_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   851→                \"gt_itl_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n   852→                \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n   853→                \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n   854→                \"blis_itl_ms\": blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n   855→                \"blis_completed\": blis[\"completed_requests\"],\n   856→                \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n   857→                \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n   858→                \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n   859→            })\n   860→        else:\n   861→            print(f\"  {dirname}: BLIS FAILED\")\n   862→\n   863→    return h2_results\n   864→\n   865→\n   866→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   867→# H3: Additive correction factors\n   868→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   869→def run_h3(h1_results, experiments, optimized_artifacts, tmpdir):\n   870→    \"\"\"H3: Test additive/multiplicative correction factors on TTFT and ITL.\"\"\"\n   871→    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n   872→    print(\"H3: Additive Correction Factors\")\n   873→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n   874→\n   875→    if not h1_results:\n   876→        print(\"  SKIP: No H1 results to compute corrections from.\")\n   877→        return [], {}\n   878→\n   879→    # Compute TTFT and ITL residuals per model\n   880→    model_residuals = {}\n   881→    for r in h1_results:\n   882→        model = r[\"model\"]\n   883→        if model not in model_residuals:\n   884→            model_residuals[model] = {\"ttft\": [], \"itl\": [], \"gt_ttft\": [], \"gt_itl\": []}\n   885→        model_residuals[model][\"ttft\"].append(r[\"blis_ttft_ms\"] - r[\"gt_ttft_ms\"])\n   886→        model_residuals[model][\"itl\"].append(r[\"blis_itl_ms\"] - r[\"gt_itl_ms\"])\n   887→        model_residuals[model][\"gt_ttft\"].append(r[\"gt_ttft_ms\"])\n   888→        model_residuals[model][\"gt_itl\"].append(r[\"gt_itl_ms\"])\n   889→\n   890→    # Compute correction factors per model\n   891→    corrections = {}\n   892→    print(\"\\n--- Residual Analysis ---\")\n   893→    for model, resid in model_residuals.items():\n   894→        ttft_residuals = np.array(resid[\"ttft\"])\n   895→        itl_residuals = np.array(resid[\"itl\"])\n   896→        gt_ttft = np.array(resid[\"gt_ttft\"])\n   897→        gt_itl = np.array(resid[\"gt_itl\"])\n   898→\n   899→        # TTFT correction: blis_ttft = alpha * gt_ttft + beta\n   900→        # We want corrected = blis / alpha - beta/alpha\n   901→        # But simpler: compute additive offset = mean(gt_ttft - blis_ttft)\n   902→        ttft_offset = float(np.mean(-ttft_residuals))  # Add this to blis_ttft\n   903→        # Multiplicative: gt / blis ratio\n   904→        blis_ttft_arr = gt_ttft + ttft_residuals  # = blis_ttft\n   905→        ttft_ratio = float(np.mean(gt_ttft / np.maximum(blis_ttft_arr, 0.01)))\n   906→\n   907→        # ITL correction\n   908→        itl_offset = float(np.mean(-itl_residuals))\n   909→        blis_itl_arr = gt_itl + itl_residuals\n   910→        itl_ratio = float(np.mean(gt_itl / np.maximum(blis_itl_arr, 0.01)))\n   911→\n   912→        corrections[model] = {\n   913→            \"ttft_additive_ms\": ttft_offset,\n   914→            \"ttft_multiplicative\": ttft_ratio,\n   915→            \"itl_additive_ms\": itl_offset,\n   916→            \"itl_multiplicative\": itl_ratio,\n   917→            \"ttft_residual_mean_ms\": float(np.mean(ttft_residuals)),\n   918→            \"ttft_residual_std_ms\": float(np.std(ttft_residuals)),\n   919→            \"itl_residual_mean_ms\": float(np.mean(itl_residuals)),\n   920→            \"itl_residual_std_ms\": float(np.std(itl_residuals)),\n   921→        }\n   922→        print(f\"  {model}: TTFT residual={np.mean(ttft_residuals):.1f}±{np.std(ttft_residuals):.1f}ms, \"\n   923→              f\"ITL residual={np.mean(itl_residuals):.2f}±{np.std(itl_residuals):.2f}ms\")\n   924→        print(f\"    TTFT correction: additive={ttft_offset:.1f}ms, multiplicative={ttft_ratio:.2f}x\")\n   925→        print(f\"    ITL correction: additive={itl_offset:.2f}ms, multiplicative={itl_ratio:.2f}x\")\n   926→\n   927→    # Apply corrections via QueueingTime and OutputTokenProcessingTime adjustments\n   928→    print(\"\\n--- Applying Corrections ---\")\n   929→    # Strategy: increase step_overhead_us (the main knob controlling E2E under-prediction)\n   930→    # and adjust queueing_time intercept (controls TTFT)\n   931→    h3_results = []\n   932→\n   933→    for exp in experiments:\n   934→        model = exp[\"meta\"][\"model\"]\n   935→        dirname = exp[\"dirname\"]\n   936→\n   937→        canonical = model\n   938→        for group_key, variants in MODEL_GROUPS.items():\n   939→            if model in variants:\n   940→                canonical = group_key\n   941→                break\n   942→\n   943→        optimized_art = optimized_artifacts.get(canonical)\n   944→        if optimized_art is None:\n   945→            continue\n   946→\n   947→        # Get the artifact to use (handling variants)\n   948→        if model != canonical and model in MODEL_ARTIFACT_MAP:\n   949→            variant_base = load_artifact(model)\n   950→            variant_params, variant_names = artifact_to_param_vector(variant_base)\n   951→            canon_base = load_artifact(canonical)\n   952→            canon_initial, canon_names = artifact_to_param_vector(canon_base)\n   953→            canon_optimized, _ = artifact_to_param_vector(optimized_art)\n   954→            new_params = np.copy(variant_params)\n   955→            for i, name in enumerate(variant_names):\n   956→                if i < len(canon_names) and name == canon_names[i]:\n   957→                    if canon_initial[i] != 0:\n   958→                        new_params[i] = variant_params[i] * (canon_optimized[i] / canon_initial[i])\n   959→                    else:\n   960→                        new_params[i] = canon_optimized[i]\n   961→            corrected_art = param_vector_to_artifact(new_params, variant_names, variant_base)\n   962→        else:\n   963→            corrected_art = copy.deepcopy(optimized_art)\n   964→\n   965→        # Apply TTFT correction: increase queueing time intercept\n   966→        corr = corrections.get(model, corrections.get(canonical, {}))\n   967→        ttft_add = corr.get(\"ttft_additive_ms\", 0) * 1000  # Convert ms → us\n   968→        if corrected_art.get(\"queueing_time\"):\n   969→            corrected_art[\"queueing_time\"][\"intercept\"] += ttft_add\n   970→        else:\n   971→            corrected_art[\"queueing_time\"] = {\n   972→                \"model_type\": \"linear\",\n   973→                \"intercept\": ttft_add,\n   974→                \"feature_coefficients\": {},\n   975→            }\n   976→\n   977→        # Apply ITL correction: adjust output_token_processing_time\n   978→        itl_add = corr.get(\"itl_additive_ms\", 0) * 1000  # ms → us\n   979→        corrected_art[\"output_token_processing_time_us\"] = max(\n   980→            0, corrected_art.get(\"output_token_processing_time_us\", 0) + itl_add\n   981→        )\n   982→\n   983→        art_path = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"h3_{dirname}.json\")\n   984→        with open(art_path, \"w\") as f:\n   985→            json.dump(corrected_art, f)\n   986→\n   987→        csv_path, horizon_us = os.path.join(tmpdir, f\"{dirname}_trace.csv\"), None\n   988→        # Recompute horizon\n   989→        with open(exp[\"lifecycle_path\"]) as f:\n   990→            lc_data = json.load(f)\n   991→        arrivals = [e[\"start_time\"] for e in lc_data]\n   992→        duration_s = max(arrivals) - min(arrivals)\n   993→        horizon_us = int((duration_s + 120) * 1_000_000)\n   994→\n   995→        blis = run_blis_trace(\n   996→            csv_path, exp[\"exp_config\"], exp[\"kv_blocks\"], art_path,\n   997→            horizon_us, exp[\"cpu_kv_blocks\"],\n   998→        )\n   999→\n  1000→        if blis:\n  1001→            e2e_err = compute_error(blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n  1002→            ttft_err = compute_error(blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n  1003→            itl_err = compute_error(blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"], exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000)\n  1004→\n  1005→            # Get H1 baseline for comparison\n  1006→            h1_match = [r for r in h1_results if r[\"experiment\"] == dirname]\n  1007→            h1_e2e = h1_match[0][\"e2e_error\"] * 100 if h1_match else None\n  1008→\n  1009→            print(f\"  {dirname}: E2E={e2e_err*100:.1f}%\"\n  1010→                  + (f\" (H1: {h1_e2e:.1f}%)\" if h1_e2e else \"\")\n  1011→                  + f\", TTFT={ttft_err*100:.1f}%, ITL={itl_err*100:.1f}%\")\n  1012→\n  1013→            h3_results.append({\n  1014→                \"experiment\": dirname,\n  1015→                \"model\": model,\n  1016→                \"workload\": exp[\"meta\"][\"workload\"],\n  1017→                \"tp\": exp[\"meta\"][\"tp\"],\n  1018→                \"gt_e2e_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"e2e_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n  1019→                \"gt_ttft_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"ttft_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n  1020→                \"gt_itl_ms\": exp[\"gt\"][\"itl_mean_s\"] * 1000,\n  1021→                \"blis_e2e_ms\": blis[\"e2e_mean_ms\"],\n  1022→                \"blis_ttft_ms\": blis[\"ttft_mean_ms\"],\n  1023→                \"blis_itl_ms\": blis[\"itl_mean_ms\"],\n  1024→                \"blis_completed\": blis[\"completed_requests\"],\n  1025→                \"e2e_error\": e2e_err,\n  1026→                \"ttft_error\": ttft_err,\n  1027→                \"itl_error\": itl_err,\n  1028→                \"h1_e2e_error\": h1_match[0][\"e2e_error\"] if h1_match else None,\n  1029→            })\n  1030→\n  1031→    return h3_results, corrections\n  1032→\n  1033→\n  1034→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  1035→# Main\n  1036→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  1037→def write_results_csv(results, path):\n  1038→    if not results:\n  1039→        return\n  1040→    all_keys = set()\n  1041→    for r in results:\n  1042→        all_keys.update(r.keys())\n  1043→    fieldnames = sorted(all_keys)\n  1044→    with open(path, \"w\", newline=\"\") as f:\n  1045→        writer = csv.DictWriter(f, fieldnames=fieldnames)\n  1046→        writer.writeheader()\n  1047→        writer.writerows(results)\n  1048→\n  1049→\n  1050→def main():\n  1051→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n  1052→    print(\"Round 3, Idea 3: E2E Calibration via Direct E2E Objective\")\n  1053→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n  1054→\n  1055→    # Ensure binary exists\n  1056→    if not os.path.isfile(BINARY_PATH):\n  1057→        print(\"Building simulation_worker...\")\n  1058→        build = subprocess.run(\n  1059→            [\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", BINARY_PATH, \"main.go\"],\n  1060→            cwd=REPO_ROOT, capture_output=True, text=True,\n  1061→        )\n  1062→        if build.returncode != 0:\n  1063→            print(f\"Build failed: {build.stderr}\", file=sys.stderr)\n  1064→            sys.exit(1)\n  1065→\n  1066→    experiments = discover_experiments()\n  1067→    print(f\"\\nFound {len(experiments)} experiments with lifecycle data.\")\n  1068→\n  1069→    if not experiments:\n  1070→        print(\"ERROR: No experiments found!\", file=sys.stderr)\n  1071→        sys.exit(1)\n  1072→\n  1073→    with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n  1074→        # H1: CMA-ES with trace replay\n  1075→        h1_results, initial_results, opt_logs, optimized_artifacts = run_h1(experiments, tmpdir)\n  1076→\n  1077→        # H2: Workload-spec mode with optimized coefficients\n  1078→        h2_results = run_h2(experiments, optimized_artifacts, tmpdir)\n  1079→\n  1080→        # H3: Additive correction factors\n  1081→        h3_results, corrections = run_h3(h1_results, experiments, optimized_artifacts, tmpdir)\n  1082→\n  1083→    # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  1084→    # Write all results\n  1085→    # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  1086→    h1_dir = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"h1-trace-e2e-opt\")\n  1087→    h2_dir = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"h2-workload-spec-opt\")\n  1088→    h3_dir = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \"h3-additive-corrections\")\n  1089→\n  1090→    os.makedirs(h1_dir, exist_ok=True)\n  1091→    os.makedirs(h2_dir, exist_ok=True)\n  1092→    os.makedirs(h3_dir, exist_ok=True)\n  1093→\n  1094→    # H1 outputs\n  1095→    write_results_csv(h1_results, os.path.join(h1_dir, \"e2e_opt_results.csv\"))\n  1096→    if h1_results:\n  1097→        ok = [r for r in h1_results if \"e2e_error\" in r]\n  1098→        h1_summary = {\n  1099→            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n  1100→            \"mean_e2e_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1101→            \"mean_ttft_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"ttft_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1102→            \"mean_itl_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1103→            \"e2e_under_10pct\": sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.10),\n  1104→            \"e2e_under_15pct\": sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.15),\n  1105→            \"e2e_under_25pct\": sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.25),\n  1106→            \"initial_mean_e2e_pct\": np.mean([\n  1107→                initial_results.get(r[\"experiment\"], {}).get(\"e2e_error\", 1.0)\n  1108→                for r in ok\n  1109→            ]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1110→            \"optimization_logs\": opt_logs,\n  1111→            \"per_experiment\": ok,\n  1112→        }\n  1113→        with open(os.path.join(h1_dir, \"summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n  1114→            json.dump(h1_summary, f, indent=2)\n  1115→\n  1116→    # H2 outputs\n  1117→    write_results_csv(h2_results, os.path.join(h2_dir, \"workload_spec_results.csv\"))\n  1118→    if h2_results:\n  1119→        ok = [r for r in h2_results if \"e2e_error\" in r]\n  1120→        h2_summary = {\n  1121→            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n  1122→            \"mean_e2e_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1123→            \"mean_ttft_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"ttft_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1124→            \"mean_itl_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1125→            \"e2e_under_50pct\": sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.50),\n  1126→            \"per_experiment\": ok,\n  1127→        }\n  1128→        with open(os.path.join(h2_dir, \"summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n  1129→            json.dump(h2_summary, f, indent=2)\n  1130→\n  1131→    # H3 outputs\n  1132→    write_results_csv(h3_results, os.path.join(h3_dir, \"correction_results.csv\"))\n  1133→    if h3_results:\n  1134→        ok = [r for r in h3_results if \"e2e_error\" in r]\n  1135→        h3_summary = {\n  1136→            \"n_experiments\": len(ok),\n  1137→            \"mean_e2e_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1138→            \"mean_ttft_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"ttft_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1139→            \"mean_itl_error_pct\": np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100 if ok else None,\n  1140→            \"corrections\": corrections,\n  1141→            \"per_experiment\": ok,\n  1142→        }\n  1143→        with open(os.path.join(h3_dir, \"summary.json\"), \"w\") as f:\n  1144→            json.dump(h3_summary, f, indent=2)\n  1145→\n  1146→    # Print final summary\n  1147→    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\n  1148→    print(\"FINAL SUMMARY\")\n  1149→    print(\"=\" * 70)\n  1150→\n  1151→    for label, results in [(\"H1 (trace+CMA-ES)\", h1_results),\n  1152→                           (\"H2 (workload-spec)\", h2_results),\n  1153→                           (\"H3 (corrections)\", h3_results)]:\n  1154→        ok = [r for r in results if \"e2e_error\" in r]\n  1155→        if ok:\n  1156→            mean_e2e = np.mean([r[\"e2e_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100\n  1157→            mean_ttft = np.mean([r[\"ttft_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100\n  1158→            mean_itl = np.mean([r[\"itl_error\"] for r in ok]) * 100\n  1159→            under_10 = sum(1 for r in ok if r[\"e2e_error\"] < 0.10)\n  1160→            print(f\"\\n{label}: E2E={mean_e2e:.1f}%, TTFT={mean_ttft:.1f}%, \"\n  1161→                  f\"ITL={mean_itl:.1f}%, E2E<10%={under_10}/{len(ok)}\")\n  1162→        else:\n  1163→            print(f\"\\n{label}: No results\")\n  1164→\n  1165→    print(\"\\nDone!\")\n  1166→\n  1167→\n  1168→if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n  1169→    main()\n  1170→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017vgie1jSaXiJSc9cebn2B7","session_id":"6c146fd0-2769-4d18-b481-0819d4602c26","uuid":"2ce8683d-5c61-4164-8967-fbfae3aa867b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01JgcDD4gDQcMemUuUQ4nuVe","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_011s6A6N4BeZzXddoinaswn6","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-1-constrained-cmaes/hypotheses/h-stepml/shared/sampling_analysis.py"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":23456,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017vgie1jSaXiJSc9cebn2B7","session_id":"6c146fd0-2769-4d18-b481-0819d4602c26","uuid":"73f0f6a2-afa8-4e00-b83e-265eb17bffd9"}
