{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01HB1ACdSsodXubSQ42fCPZM","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n**CMA-ES for Simulator Calibration:** This experiment uses Covariance Matrix Adaptation Evolution Strategy (CMA-ES) as a derivative-free optimizer to calibrate a discrete-event simulator. The key insight is treating the entire BLIS simulator as a black-box function `f(params) → E2E_error`, which allows joint optimization of ~14-23 latency model parameters without needing gradients. Round 4's innovation is adding ITL constraints to prevent the optimizer from finding degenerate solutions (like inflating `output_token_processing_time_us` to implausible values just to minimize E2E).\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\nLet me build the binary first, then check if CMA-ES is available in the Python environment."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c146fd0-2769-4d18-b481-0819d4602c26","uuid":"cefdbd10-659f-4ca3-bdab-27885b526e95"}
