{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01N9ZE657RZAd6QBwdNqjXHe","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pipeline verified. 10 experiments, 4 model groups. The R3 baseline for llama-2-7b roleplay shows 22.2% E2E / 91.1% ITL — exactly the problem the constrained approach aims to fix.\n\nNow let me think about execution strategy. The full `main()` function runs:\n1. H1 (alpha=0.5): 4 models × ~100 evals × ~10s/eval ≈ 67 min\n2. H2 (3 alphas × 4 models): 3 × H1 time ≈ 200 min  \n3. H3 (LOMO): just artifact evaluation, ~5 min\n4. H4 (LOWO): just artifact evaluation, ~5 min\n\n**BUT**: H2 already includes alpha=0.5, so H1 is redundant if we go straight to H2. The script however uses H1 as a short-circuit check first. Since R3's E2E was 15.1% and we're constraining it, H1 should be ≤25% easily. Let me run the full experiment directly."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c146fd0-2769-4d18-b481-0819d4602c26","uuid":"2a014142-019b-4371-a554-ee273e17cc13"}
